title: cream cheese mints
directions: Mix and knead like pie dough. Roll in balls, the size of marble. Place one side in a small amount of sugar. Press sugar side down in the mold. Unmold at once on waxed paper. (If you wish a firmer mixture, add more powdered sugar.)

title: fred's spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large pot brown turkey in 1/4 cup olive oil.
Then add next four ingredients and saute until tender.

title: tv dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except last 2.
Pour into greased 12 x 18-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: tomato eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant; slice into 1/8-inch slices.
Salt eggplant on both sides; set aside 15 minutes.
Layer eggplant in a 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Thinly slice tomatoes; layer over eggplant.
Sprinkle tomatoes with pepper, garlic salt and oregano to your liking. (Remember:
Oregano is heavy; use sparingly!)
Sprinkle cheese over top of casserole.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes at 375°. Uncover; bake an additional 10 minutes or until cheese is fully melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Combine sugar, half and half and salt, then stir in butter. Microwave on High for 10 minutes, stirring once during cooking. Stir in pecans and let sit for 1 minute.
Stir for 4 to 4 1/2 minutes until thick and creamy.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: classic karo pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir until well blended, eggs, corn syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife comes out clean. Serves 8.

title: vanilla cream coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk.
Cook and stir over heat until bubbly, about 2 minutes.

title: strawberry sipper
directions: Place berries, apple juice, mineral water and lemon juice in a blender (also ice).
Process on medium speed until just smooth and frothy.
Pour into glasses over additional ice, if desired. Garnish with mint sprigs, if desired.

title: scrumptious sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish and bake 20 minutes (or until set) at 400°.

title: cheese and rice casserole
directions: Heat water, rice, salt, mustard, red pepper sauce and pepper to boiling, stirring once or twice; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 14 minutes.
(Do not lift cover or stir.) Remove from heat.
Fluff rice lightly with a fork; cover and let steam 5 to 10 minutes.

title: macaroni olive salad
directions: Gradually add macaroni and salt to rapidly boiling water so water continues to boil.
Cook, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Drain in colander; rinse with cold water and drain again.
Blend together sour cream, mayonnaise, milk, dry mustard, basil leaves and lemon juice in large bowl.
Add macaroni, vegetables and olive slices.
Toss until combined.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cover and chill for several hours.

title: pillsbury cream cheese rolls
directions: Mix until creamy the eggs (take 1 tablespoon egg white out and save), vanilla, sugar and cream cheese.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread 1 can rolls on the bottom; pinch together.
Spread mixture on top rolls.
Spread 1 can rolls on top; pinch together (with egg white).

title: chicken polynesian
directions: Combine cranberries, dressing and soup.
Place chicken breasts in casserole or baking pan.
Pour sauce over chicken and bake at 350°, uncovered, for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Pour sauce over rice and chicken.

title: buttermilk baked chicken
directions: Dip chicken into 1/2 cup buttermilk, then roll in flour. Season with salt and pepper.
Melt butter or oleo in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put chicken in pan, skin side down, and bake, uncovered, at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: rose kennedy's boston cream pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in 1/2 the sugar. Gradually beat egg yolks and other liquids until light.
Beat in remaining sugar.
Combine egg yolks and egg whites.
Add remaining ingredients by folding and cutting in.
Pour into a buttered pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken and take meat off bones.
Mix chicken, soup and broth.
Put in baking dish.
Mix crackers, butter and poppy seed. Sprinkle over top of chicken.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: chili sauce
directions: Combine chopped vegetables, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Tie spices in a bag.
Cook until about 1/2 original amount.
Pour in jar and seal.

title: easy taco dinner
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Drain and add taco seasoning and water.
Let simmer about 10 minutes or until thick.
Combine shredded lettuce, onion, tomatoes and cheese.
Heat beans and drain.

title: crisp
directions: You will need a clear glass bowl, pie dish and measuring cup.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix cans of shrimp soup with milk over low heat; use last. Layer in casserole the rice, crab meat, shrimp and cheese, using all ingredients.
Pour cream of shrimp over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: peanut cream frosting
directions: Combine marshmallow cream and milk, mixing with electric mixer until well blended.
Add peanut butter, beating until light and fluffy.

title: oven stew
directions: Put all together in roaster.
Bake at 250°, covered, for 5 hours.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 15-20 minutes.
Good for beef, pork, and chicken.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers.
Makes two cups.

title: cherry yum yum(monroe's favorite)
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with finely crumbled vanilla wafers.
Use 2/3 of this mixture to make crust in bottom of dish.
Press firmly in place.
Mix sugar, room temperature cream cheese and thawed Cool Whip.
Put 1/2 of Cool Whip mixture over crust.
Pour cherry pie filling over creamed mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip mixture over pie filling.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs and chill.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soften yeast and dissolve in 1 teaspoon sugar in water. Add milk, which has been cooled to lukewarm.
Add shortening, sugar and salt. Add beaten eggs and mix well. Add flour to make soft dough. Let stand 10 minutes. Knead until smooth and elastic. Place in large greased bowl.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips and butter; cook and stir over very low heat until chips are melted and smooth.
Add sweetened condensed milk; mix well.

title: chile quesadillas(makes 18 pieces)
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Grate the cheese.
Cut the chiles in thin slices.
Wrap the tortillas in foil and warm in the oven 10 minutes.
Put 1/6 of the cheese on half of one tortilla.
Top with chile slices.
Beat the egg.
Brush around the edges of the tortilla.
Fold the tortilla over the filling and press the edge to seal.
Repeat.
Cover the finished quesadillas with a towel while preparing the rest.
Heat about 1/2-inch of oil (lard) in large frying pan.
Fry the quesadillas, turning once until golden, 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Cut each into 3 wedges and serve hot.
Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix Jell-O.
Let set until thick but not firm.
Beat margarine and sugar together until fluffy.
Mix milk and cornstarch; cook until thick.
Let cool, then mix with sugar mixture.
Beat until fluffy.
Drain pineapple; mix it,
ground nuts and vanilla with other mixture.
In an 8 x 8-inch pan, place whole crackers in bottom.
Pour filling in.
Place another layer of crackers.
Pour Jell-O on top of this.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: ice cream cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, make the following layers.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
Cream the butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with lemonade, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Drop 2-inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Brush with remaining lemonade and sprinkle with sugar.

title: cantaloupe pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine sugar and flour. Add all other ingredients. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: pasta pronto
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Toss with oil, chickpeas and parsley. Shake on Parmesan.

title: green gelatin
directions: Beat until well blended with mixer, then add 1 large can of crushed pineapple with its juice.
Refrigerate.

title: lasagna
directions: Take sausage out of casing and leave in chunks.
Mix Ricotta cheese, egg and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Assemble:
Put sauce on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Layer noodles, Mozzarella cheese, sauce and Ricotta cheese 2 times.
Top noodles with Mozzarella; sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ham and noodle casserole(serves 6)
directions: Melt butter/margarine.
Gradually add flour, salt and pepper. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add parsley flakes, noodles and ham.
Fold in eggs.
Pour into lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cantonese chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine chicken with soy sauce, cornstarch, 1 teaspoon chicken broth and pepper.
Marinate 1/2 hour.
Heat oil in wok or large skillet; stir-fry chicken and onions for five minutes.
Add broccoli, snow peas, carrots, water chestnuts and ginger; stir-fry for 10 minutes.
Add broth.
Cover; heat for 2 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: iced grand marnier souffle
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar.
Gradually fold in whipped cream. Fold in Grand Marnier.
Pour into small dishes.
Freeze 2 hours or until frozen.

title: "easy" barbecue chicken
directions: Put chicken in an iron skillet.
Add barbecue sauce and Coke. Cover with a lid and cook on medium for 45 minutes to an hour. Turn every so often.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix chicken, vermicelli noodles, tomatoes, olives, onions and Parmesan cheese.

title: nut cookies
directions: Mix as usual.
Add nuts, peanut butter or raisins or nuts and raisins or coconut.
Form dough into balls.
Bake at 350° to 375° (depends on your oven) until lightly brown.

title: berry banana walnut bread
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda, nutmeg and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
In another bowl, stir together eggs, sugar, mashed berries, banana, oil and orange peel.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until combined.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes clean. Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.
Wrap and store overnight.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Lightly coat 12 muffin cups with Pam. In bowl, combine egg, cereal, bananas, raisins, vegetable oil and milk. Let stand 10 minutes. In 2-cup measuring cup, combine dry ingredients. Stir into banana mixture. Spoon into prepared muffin tin. Bake 20 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Cook rice as directed on package. Mix rice, soup and corn in baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Stir ingredients in large Pyrex pitcher or measuring cup. Microwave on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir and microwave another 1 1/2 minutes.
Chill for 2 hours or until firm.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll into a coating of chopped nuts, coconut or jimmies. Chill on cooking sheet.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except pastry shell; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Cut a hole in a piece of foil (about 8 inches in diameter) to cover the pastry so it won't burn.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes longer or until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Cool.
Garnish as desired.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove chicken from bone and cut in pieces.
Place in casserole dish or pan.
Spread celery soup over chicken.
Pour broth over mixture and sprinkle vegetables over this.
Melt margarine in quart jar in microwave.
Add milk and flour to jar.
Shake until mixed well.
Pour over chicken mixture. Bake 1 hour or until top is brown.

title: sausage-rice stuffing casserole
directions: Saute sausage, celery, onion and mushrooms in a large skillet until lightly browned.
Combine ingredients and place in 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or stuff a large turkey.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix together and store in airtight container.
Add 2 teaspoons to 1 cup of boiling water per serving.
Makes about 75 cups.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Cook barley and rinse.
Saute vegetables with butter in soup pot.
Add stock and meat; simmer 1 hour.
Add barley and tomatoes and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: minnie's delicious cookies
directions: Refrigerate for 4 to 5 hours.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package. Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool in pan. Prepare pudding using 2 cups chilled milk.
Fold well the drained crushed pineapple into pudding.
Spread on cool cake. Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut, nuts and cherry slices. Refrigerate.

title: glazed cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for 1 hour.
Shape into balls.
Dip quickly in water, then into sugar.
They flatten as they bake.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook pasta according to directions. Cook sausage. When	half done, add green pepper and onion. When done, drain. Drain pasta. Put all ingredients in large pan except for cheese. Mix well. Pour 1/2 of mixture in large baking dish. Put a layer of Mozzarella cheese. Pour remaining mixture on top of cheese. Put remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° until warm and cheese has melted.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
While rice is cooking, heat 1 c
milk, sugar and salt in a medium sauce pan. Add cooked rice to milk mixture and continue to cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
In a small bowl, beat egg with remaining milk. Gradually pour into hot rice mixture, stirring constantly. continue to cook for 5 minutes. Add vanilla or cinnamon, if desired.
Serve warm or cold. Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and add seasoned salt to taste.
Shape into a ball and roll in nuts.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies.
Mix pudding and mousse.
Crush Heath bars and nuts.
Begin to layer 1/2 of brownies, 1/2 of pudding, 1/2 of candy and nuts and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Repeat layering.
Decorate top with mousse.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Toss bread, ham and cheese cubes in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Mix flour and dry mustard; sprinkle over mixture in pan.
Drizzle butter over top.
Mix eggs and milk together.
Add dash of Tabasco.
Pour over mixture in pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tasty corn bread
directions: Beat eggs, then blend in sour cream, oil, baking powder, salt, sugar and corn.
Blend in corn meal last.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chutney cheese
directions: Blend all ingredients well.
Chill for at least 4 hours.
Top with toasted almonds.
Serve with crackers.

title: beefy cheese ball
directions: In blender, dice onions and beef.
Mix with other ingredients. Chill in the refrigerator until slightly firm, shape into a ball and roll in finely chopped pecans.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Wash barley and drain.
Add barley to water and beef broth. Cook over medium heat about 1 hour.
Add all other ingredients, breaking up corned beef with a fork.
Cook additional 30 minutes. Serves approximately 8 to 10.

title: quick bread
directions: Set aside to rise until double.
Knead and put in loaf pan. Let rise until about 1-inch from top of pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Add other ingredients; stir only until blended.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stuff
directions: Shred potatoes, cabbage, carrots and onion.
Mix in order given.
Put 3/4 beef in skillet (11-inch).
Layer vegetables as listed on top of beef.
Crumble beef on top.
Pour soup on top. Add grated cheese last.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: salmon party ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts and parsley.
Shape mixture into a ball.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours (no longer than 4 days).
Mix nuts and parsley and coat ball.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In skillet, brown the ground beef and onion; drain off grease. Add to the rest of mixture. Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: apple date cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, soda, salt, cinnamon and allspice. Combine eggs, pie filling, oil and vanilla; stir in dates and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares. Serve with dollop of whipped topping.
Serves 12.

title: robin's split pea soup
directions: Put water and ham in pot.
Cook 1 hour on medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients and cook another hour.
May need to add more water if becomes dry.

title: waterloo squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread out in a 9 x 13 baking pan which has been lightly sprayed on the bottom. Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over mixture. Blend cream cheese, eggs and powdered sugar and pour over top. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Cool and cut into squares. This is very rich.

title: devilburgers
directions: Mix ground beef with tomatoes or sauce (can use blender or food processor).
Add other ingredients.
Better knead mixture by hand for thoroughness.
Spread mixture 1/4-inch thick on slice of day old bread, making sure the meat entirely covers the bread to its very edges or the bread will burn.
Cook under broiler and when meat is done, top with narrow slices of cheese which will melt when put back under broiler.
When meat shows little brown crusty place and cheese melts, serve with sweet pickles, olives, and drink.

title: mexican sausage and salsa
directions: Start with a large microwave casserole dish with cover.
Put tomato sauce and jar of salsa.
Take sausage out of casing and cut into small pieces; add in sauce.
Add garlic, onion and jalapeno peppers.
Microwave 20 minutes at 50%.
Heat, stirring every 2 minutes.
Take out of microwave when done; let cool 2 minutes, then add rice or pasta to sauce.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place oleo in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Place oleo in oven to melt.
Combine next 4 ingredients.
Beat well.
Pour batter over melted oleo; pour peaches over batter. Bake one hour.

title: mom's chocolate chip muffins
directions: Sift ingredients into bowl; make well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir quickly until just mixed.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400°
for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 muffins.

title: chicken bake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and distribute the rice evenly over the bottom.
Sprinkle salt and pepper and vegetable pieces as desired.
Lay on the chicken.
Mix soup and water together.
Pour over ingredients in dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° until chicken is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
About halfway through the cooking, remove from oven and turn the chicken.
About 15 minutes before end of baking, remove foil for browning.

title: cheese and ham balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Mix well and chill. Shape into 2 balls and coat with pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: real easy pickles
directions: Slice vegetables and sprinkle with 1/3 cup salt; cover with crushed ice for 3 hours.
Drain.
Bring to a boil: vinegar, mustard seed and sugar.
While still hot, pour over drained vegetables.
Refrigerate.
Do not can.
I put these pickles in a gallon glass jar.
They are nice and crisp and will keep up to one year in the refrigerator.

title: cranberry nut pudding pie
directions: Spread cranberries on bottom of a buttered 9-inch pie pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.

title: yucky cake
directions: Mix 1 egg, 1 stick butter and cake mix until like cookie batter.
Spread in greased oblong pan or glass dish. Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar; pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put oleo into flat Pyrex dish and put in oven to melt and get hot. Place flour and seasonings into brown bag or plastic bag and drop 3 or 4 pieces of chicken at a time in and shake to coat.
Place pieces in melted oleo and bake for 30 minutes.
Turn and cook 30 minutes longer or until browned.
Serve on hot platter.

title: cranberry crunch salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add water to pineapple juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Heat.
Dissolve Jello in liquid.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Stir to blend.
Pour into 8x11 inch dish. Chill until firm.

title: cornbread loaf
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl, mixing well. Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Add to dry mixture, stirring until smooth. Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool loaf in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Serve warm or cool completely on wire rack.

title: instant coffee cake
directions: In a large bowl mix flour, sugar, vanilla, eggs, margarine, coffee and water.
Mix on low speed for 2 minutes.
Pour in greased pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: small nut rolls
directions: Mix flour and shortening.
Crumble in cake of yeast.
Add egg yolks, beaten with some of evaporated milk.
Add remainder of milk to flour mixture.
Knead well and refrigerate overnight.
Roll a ball of dough as you would for pie, using sugar instead of flour. Cut into triangles.
Spread with nut filling and roll up like crescent rolls.
Roll in sugar before putting on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 8 dozen.
Can also use apricot filling.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Add wafers and milk.
Mix well.
Add nuts and coconut.
Cook in a tube pan at 325° until done, about 45 to 55 minutes.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Peel peaches and cover with sugar.
Let stand overnight or until sugar melts.
Drain juice and measure.
Add equal parts vinegar and bring to boil with cloves and cinnamon.
Add peaches and cook until tender.
Remove spices and fill peaches in jars and seal.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar; beat well.
Add oil and beat, then add flour, spices and salt.
Add pumpkin; beat at low speed and pour in well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: puffed sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add eggs, then remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: british cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg, flour and vanilla. Drop by teaspoon and roll in oats. Bake at 300° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Melt butter; remove from heat.
Blend in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring until well blended.
Stir while cooking over low heat until thick and smooth.
Add asparagus puree, asparagus and seasonings; mix well.
Before serving, add cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted and well blended.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve on sandwiches, crackers, etc.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour in prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set. Spoon blueberry topping on top of pie.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown onion.
Add rest of ingredients; simmer for 20 minutes. Pour sauce over ribs.
Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pork chop skillet
directions: Trim excess fat from chops.
Heat in skillet until you have about 2 tablespoons drippings.
Roll chops in flour; brown in fat. Combine cheese, salt and pepper.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour batter in pan over melted butter.
Pour peaches or other fruit over batter.
Crust will rise to top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until crust is brown.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Pour cereal into large bowl.
Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine until smooth, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Pour mixture over cereals, stirring until all are evenly coated.
Pour cereal mixture into Ziploc bag with powdered sugar; shake until well coated.
Spread on cookie sheet to cool.

title: norwegian apple cake(norway)
directions: Beat eggs well, one at a time.
Sift together sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sifted ingredients and vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a well-greased 9-inch pie plate or cake pan.
May be topped with Cool Whip.

title: kimberly's play dough
directions: Combine flour, salt, cream of tartar and oil in a pan.
In a measuring cup, dissolve any flavor of Kool-Aid with water.
Add to flour mixture and cook on medium heat until it forms a ball. Remove from heat and let cool.
Knead to make smooth.
It smells fantastic!

title: marinated cucumber salad
directions: Combine cucumbers, onion, carrots and celery in a large dish; set aside.
Combine remainder of ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over vegetables, tossing lightly.
Cover and chill in refrigerator.

title: 7 can soup
directions: Brown meat and onion. Empty all cans into a large pot. Add browned meat and onion; simmer 1 hour. Makes 1 gallon of soup.

title: pickled okra
directions: Wash okra and pack loosely into sterilized pint jars.
Put 1 hot pepper pod and 1 garlic clove in each jar.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil.
Pour over okra and seal.
Let stand eight weeks before using.
If pepper pods are not available, use 1/4 teaspoon of crushed, dried
hot red pepper for each jar.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil eggs.
Boil broccoli.
Lay broccoli in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Cover with mushroom soup, no water.
Dice eggs on top of soup. Cover with sliced cheese.
Add Ritz crackers to cover cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees until bubbly.

title: best ever fluffy pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks very light.
Blend in the melted butter; add the sugar.
Add the flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix.
Add buttermilk; mix until smooth.
Fold in lightly, 3 egg whites, beaten stiff.
Bake, eat.
They are light and fluffy, but crispy outside.

title: fruit bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add sifted ingredients; mix well.
Stir in nuts and fruit; turn into buttered pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
While warm, cut into small wedges.

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Combine light sour cream and dip mix in medium bowl. Stir in artichokes, spinach and pimentos. Slice off top of round loaf of bread. Hollow out center of bread, leaving 1-inch of shell. Reserve bread pieces for dipping. Spoon dip into bread shell. Serve warm or cold.

title: creamy cheddar chowder
directions: Boil the vegetables in the 2 cups of water until vegetables are soft (do not drain).
Make white sauce in separate pan.
Melt butter and stir in flour over a hot burner.
Add milk and cheese. Stir until melted.
Add undrained vegetables and chopped ham. Add 1/2 teaspoon of pepper to this mixture.
Continue heating until uniformly hot, without allowing mixture to boil.

title: three cheese manicotti
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella cheese, Ricotta and Parmesan cheeses.
Add eggs, Italian seasoning and garlic.
Mix lightly.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, evaporated milk and spices together in bowl; set aside.
Melt Cheez Whiz in double boiler.
When melted, stir in Miracle Whip mixture and stir.

title: beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a 1-pint jar.
Cover and shake until well mixed.
Add beef broth and sherry.
Heat oil in wok over medium heat.
Add broccoli and mushrooms; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Add beef; stir-fry for 1 to 2 minutes.
Add vegetables and broth mixture.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add cherry tomatoes.
Serve over rice.
May store cooking sauce in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks or freeze for longer periods.
Yields 4 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients in butter.
Add rice to water and set aside for 5 minutes.
Mix together, then add butter, pepper and onions.
Add rice, mix well, pour into dish and top with favorite grated cheese.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry supreme pie
directions: Fold strawberry yogurt into topping.
Add fruit; blend.
Spoon into crust and freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Place in refrigerator for 45 minutes before cutting.
Garnish as desired. Other flavors of yogurt may be used.

title: rice pudding
directions: Stir milk and egg into pudding.
Mix in saucepan.
Add rice and raisins. Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to boil. Cool for 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into dessert dishes. Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Refrigerate or serve warm. Recipe makes 10 servings.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar and oleo.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and bake 40 - 45 minutes at 325°. Serves 6 - 8.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar together. Add eggs, flour and spices. Mix well. Add prunes and nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: company coming mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until fork-tender; drain. Place potatoes in large bowl. Add cream cheese, sour cream, salt, pepper and paprika. Mix with an electric mixer until smooth. Place mashed potatoes in a buttered baking dish. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: raspberry punch
directions: You can also use orange-raspberry sherbet.

title: mixed fruit salad
directions: Mix fruit.
Coat with the following mixture and refrigerate for several hours.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, peas, carrots, soup, broth, salt and pepper together. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix Bisquick, milk and butter together. Pour over chicken mixture. Bake in 400° oven for 60 minutes or crust is light brown.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple with cheese.
Mix sugar and flour.
Fold into pineapple mixture.
Place into a casserole dish.
Top with crackers.
Melt oleo and pour over top.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake until brown, about 25 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage, onions and pepper. Blend in 1/2 cup sugar and salt. Toss together. Let stand while you cook the remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Pour over cabbage mixture slowly. Stir until all is coated. Let cool, then cover and refrigerate.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Combine gelatin, coconut, walnuts and milk in a large bowl. Mix until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: olive salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a quart jar.
Keeps well refrigerated.

title: holiday breakfast
directions: Mix salt, milk, mustard and eggs.
Place cubed bread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and put meat on top of that.
Pour egg mixture over the top.
Make sure the pan is greased.
Refrigerate for at least 12 hours the night before.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 350° oven for a wonder souffle breakfast.

title: seafood jacques
directions: Put scallops, wine and parsley in 3-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer 8 minutes; drain, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Saute mushrooms and onions in 2 tablespoons butter. Remove and add 3 more tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour. Put in 1 cup liquid and half and half, stirring until smooth.
Add cheese; stir until melted, then add fish, mushrooms, onions and shrimp. Serve in patty shells or on rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan; add flour and mix.
Add broth, milk and water.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Stir constantly.
Stir in vegetables, salt, rice and chicken.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato latkes (pancakes)(a channukah favorite)
directions: These are best done in an iron skillet or an electric skillet.

title: tuscan potato salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients and toss lightly. Allow to stand about 1/2 hour to blend flavors before serving at room temperature.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first seven ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole dish. Mix remaining ingredients.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese; mix thoroughly. Divide meat mixture into thirds.
Pat 1/3 in bottom of 9 1/2 x 5 x 3 loaf pan.
Cover with half the cheese.
Repeat layer, ending with the meat.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: apple crunch
directions: Thinly slice apples; arrange in well-greased baking dish. Combine sugar, oats, cinnamon, flour and nuts and stir.
Pour melted butter into dry ingredients and blend until crumbly. Spread mixture over apples and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: alpine chicken casserole
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except for almonds, salad dressing and milk.
Thin salad dressing with milk in separate bowl.
Then pour mixture over combined ingredients and mix well. Pour into ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Top with almonds when finished baking.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs. Add rest of ingredients.
Place in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pineapple-nut cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients except 1 cup chopped nuts.
Form into ball and chill.
Reform ball and roll in the remaining nuts, covering the ball with nuts.
Chill several more hours before serving.
This makes a large cheese ball.
I would suggest dividing it into 2 cheese balls.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix with chives. Trim crusts from bread and cut each slice in half.
Spread 1 teaspoon cheese mixture on each half and roll up.
Wrap a slice of bacon around each and secure with a toothpick.
Place on a broiler pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn as necessary to prevent overbrowning.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In small saucepan, combine butter, sugar and water; bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 6 ounces (1 cup) semi-sweet chocolate chips and vanilla extract. Stir until chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Transfer to large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining 1 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Cool completely. Cut into 2 1/4-inch squares.
Makes sixteen 2 1/4-inch squares.

title: cantaloupe green salad
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in large serving bowl.
Next combine remaining ingredients.
Stir with a wire whisk.
Pour dressing over cantaloupe mixture.
Cover and chill.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Add Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk and water; mix.
Add pudding mix until well blended, chill 5 minutes.
Beat whipping cream and fold into mixture.
Delicious!

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and peanuts in heavy skillet. Bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soda; pour into well-buttered pan.

title: cherry almond mousse pie (very good)
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, cook and stir 1/2 cup milk and chocolate until the chocolate is melted and mixture is thickened (about 4 to 5 minutes).
Stir in 1/4 teaspoon extract.
Pour into pastry shell.
Set aside.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Fry bacon and crumble into kidney beans. In bacon drippings, saut vegetables. Cook until well wilted, but not browned, stirring frequently. Add beans and remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer about 30 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: polar hot chocolate
directions: Stir chocolate with the peppermint stick.
Bite off the tip and sip the hot chocolate through it like a straw.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix marshmallows and pineapple.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In saucepan, mix juice, sugar, egg, flour and vinegar. Boil until thick and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, combine the two mixtures and add apples, nuts and Cool Whip.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 7 ingredients.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: best deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks. Mash yolks with mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well. Stuff egg whites with yolk mixture.
Garnish eggs with paprika.

title: cheese bites
directions: Combine cheeses in a bowl; mix well.
Spread half of the cheese mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Top with green chilies.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese mixture.
Beat eggs, flour and milk in a bowl.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Whip potatoes in butter.
Add remaining ingredients; beat until fluffy.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
May be prepared a day in advance and baked before serving. Serves 10.

title: pineapple-orange punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine ice cream, sherbet and pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Add ginger ale.
Mix gently.
Makes approximately 25 servings.

title: double quick rolls
directions: Put yeast into the warm water and add 1 tsp sugar from the 1/4 c. Let stand a few minutes so the yeast begins to work, then add remainder of the sugar, egg, shortening and salt.
Beat with electric mixer.
Add the flour and mix on low speed.
Have floured area ready to put the dough on.
Use flour on hand and rolling pin. Roll the dough by hand a little on the floured board, and then pat or roll the dough out less than 1/2 inch thick.
Brush melted butter over dough and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture. Raisins may be added if desired.
Roll the dough as for jelly roll. Cut in 1/2 inch slices.
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Wash potatoes and bake in conventional oven at 400° for 1 hour
or
until
done.
Let
cool.
Cut
potatoes
in half, lengthwise,
and
then
scoop
out
pulp.
Melt margarine in a heavy saucepan over low heat;
add all-purpose flour, stirring until
smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add 6
cups milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture
is
thick
and bubbly.
Add potato pulp, salt, pepper,
2 teaspoons
green
onions,
1/2 cup bacon and 1 cup grated cheese.
Cook
until heated.
Stir in sour cream.
Add extra milk, if necessary for thickness.
Garnish each bowl of soup with green onion, bacon and cheese.
Yield:
10 cups.

title: swedish tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and blend sugar.
Add egg yolk, then flour.
Roll dough into small balls, 1-inch in diameter.
Dip each one in egg white, then roll in chopped nuts.
Place cookies on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 5 minutes at 300°.
Press centers and bake 15 minutes longer.
Cool slightly.
Fill hole with jelly.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: halupki casserole
directions: Chop cabbage and put in a greased baking dish.
Brown meat and onion.
Stir in the rice.
Pour on top of cabbage.
Mix soup and water and pour over casserole.
Cover lightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pimiento cheese
directions: A number of times through the years All Saints' has held a Seder Dinner in the Parish Hall on Maundy and Thursday.
We have used both Greek and Jewish foods.

Some of the foods prepared were Carrot Tzimmes, Charoseth, Chicken Soup, Chopped Liver, Herb-roasted Leg of Lamb with Red Potatoes, Knaidlach, Lentil Soup, Roast Lamb and Potatoes and 12-Egg Sponge Cake.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together soup, onion, egg and squash.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing.
Sprinkle some of stuffing in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle some cheese on this.
Put a layer of squash next. Repeat layers and end with cheese.
Bake until bubbly at 325°.

title: the cake that won't last
directions: Do not beat this cake.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in tube pan.

title: caramel crunch bars
directions: Melt caramels with evaporated milk in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Stir together flour, oats, baking soda and salt.
Cut in oleo until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining crumb mixture on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces over baked crust.
Spread caramel mixture evenly over chocolate pieces. Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture over top.
Bake 20 minutes longer. Chill until cooled, about 2 hours.
Cut into bars.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Dip the mushrooms in melted butter and place upside-down in shallow baking pan.
Chop enough of remaining stems to make 1/4 cup and saute them with the onions in the remaining butter.
You may add more butter, if necessary. Add the sherry or white wine and lightly stir in the stuffing. Spoon this mixture into the mushroom caps and bake in 350° oven until hot, about 10 minutes.
Makes about 18 hors d'oeuvres.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: onion chicken nuggets
directions: Crush mix in pouch and combine with bread crumbs and pepper. Beat egg and water.
Dip chicken pieces (cut into 1-inch pieces) into egg/water mix, then into crumbs to coat.
Place on baking sheet.
Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.

title: pizza on a bun
directions: Grind pimentos, cheese, bacon and eggs.
Mix with chili sauce and spread on hamburger buns.
Put under broiler or in oven for 8 to 10 minutes until cheese melts and browns lightly.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Line unpricked pastry shells with a double thickness of heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 400 degrees for 5 minutes.
Remove foil; bake 5 minutes longer.

title: sherried orange dessert
directions: Peel and slice oranges into cart-wheel slices 1/4-inch thick. Into a glass bowl, arrange slices and coconut in alternating layers, ending with a layer of coconut.
Pour sherry over all and chill for at least an hour.

title: fruit freeze
directions: Soften sherbet enough to stir in diced bananas and strawberries.
Mix thoroughly in a large bowl and place in freezer until ready to serve.
Remove from freezer 15 to 20 minutes before serving.
Especially refreshing treat for warm summer days. Serves 20 to 25 people.

title: herb cheese bread
directions: Cut bread in 1-inch slices, almost to, but not through, bottom crust.
Place on a piece of foil large enough to wrap bread.
Cut Swiss cheese slices in half; place cheese slices between bread slices. Mix rest of ingredients together and melt for easy pouring.
Pour butter mixture over the bread and cheese slices. Wrap bread in foil and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 12.
Approximately 291 calories per serving.

title: special fruit cake(makes one large or three small loaves)
directions: Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Place nuts, cherries, dates and raisins in a large bowl.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt well and sift over fruit.
Make sure all fruit is coated with flour mixture.
Beat eggs until fluffy; add vanilla.
Blend eggs into fruit mixture; spoon into loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan to cake rack.

title: puzzle pieces
directions: Cream butter and sugar in a small sauce pan. Bring to a boil. Divide graham crackers and place in baking dish. Spoon mixture over graham crackers. Sprinkle nuts over evenly. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Cool. Cut.

title: rejoice! coconut carrot cake
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together and set aside.
Grate carrots and set aside.
Mix and cream the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour mixture to oil, sugar and eggs.
Add carrots, then stir in the pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
I find it best to add pineapple and juice to egg mixture before adding the flour.

title: face paint
directions: In muffin tin, mix cornstarch, water, food coloring and cold cream, blending well.
Apply to face or arms with small paint brush or cotton swab.
Makes enough to paint one face.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: crawfish fettuccine
directions: Melt butter and saute chopped onions, celery, bell pepper about 10 minutes.
Blend in flour and cover and cook for 15 minutes over medium heat.
Stir occasionally.
Add parsley and crawfish (shrimp or chicken).
Cover and cook for additional 20 minutes; stir often. Add cream cheese, pepper and garlic.
Mix well.
Cook on low heat for 20 minutes and stir often.
Don't let it stick!
Prepare fettuccine according to package directions.
Mix pasta and sauce mixture and place in large lasagna pan or two 9 x 13 dishes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake for 12 minutes at 350°.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In plastic bag or bowl, shake or toss all ingredients until vegetables are coated.
Empty into 13 x 9-inch baking dish, discard bag.
Bake, stirring once 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: easter "bird nests"
directions: Melt chocolate bar and chocolate semi-sweet chips in microwave on simmer.
When melted, stir in milk chocolate chips and stir until blended well.
Add coconut and drop by tablespoon on wax paper.
Spread on a cookie sheet.
Shape into little nests using a spoon.
While still warm, add green tinted coconut to look like grass.
Fill nests with jelly beans, pastel M&M's or small candy animals, to decorate.
Use imaginations.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Sift together, flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Add pumpkin, eggs, salad oil, nuts, milk, vanilla and chocolate chips; mix well.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix 1/2 cup water with dry ingredients.
Mix until all is wet.
Pour in double boiler.
Add 2 cups milk and stir until thick.
Careful not to let it stick.
Put over homemade biscuits and eat.
Delicious.

title: sea breeze salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water; add 2 cups cold water and let stand until Jell-O thickens. Stir in instant pudding mix and whip with mixer. Save 1 cup mixture. Add fruit cocktail to rest. Put in 9 x 13 pan and let get firm. Whip Dream Whip and fold in saved cup mixture. Spread over first layer.

title: sourdough starter
directions: In a bowl combine yeast and water.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Sprinkle flour into mixture and whisk to form a thick batter. Cover and place in a warm place (80° to 85°) for 24 hours.
The starter can be used at this point but will develop a richer flavor if left in warm place for several days.

title: rolled honey pastries(diples i)
directions: Add orange juice, lemon
juice,
whiskey
and
salt
to beaten eggs.
Gradually add
baking
powder
and flour to make soft dough.
Knead by hand to form a stiff dough, adding flour as needed, as in bread.
Take	a
piece
size of an orange and roll it out on a floured board, paper thinness.	With a pastry wheel, cut dough in strips, 2
x
3-inches.
In
a deep frying pan, drop strips in hot oil.	Using
forks, turn dough over immediately and roll loosely in jelly roll fashion.
Fry until golden brown. Drain in a colander and cool.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Combine flour, oil and sugar.
Separate 4 eggs.
Slowly mix in the yellow.
Add the cinnamon, pineapple, pecans and egg whites. Mix until thoroughly blended.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: little pizzas
directions: Saute ground beef and drain off fat.
Roll out biscuits to form flat circle.
Brush biscuits with tomato sauce.
Spread ground beef and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° until crust is lightly browned.
May vary by adding other toppings, such as green onions.

title: easy, delicious chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, salt and soda.
Add sugar and the rest of the ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Do not overbeat. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan set on wire rack.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water or can be added to dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk to dry ingredients.
Turn out on floured board.
Knead lightly.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip in melted butter and fold in half and place in pan or cookie sheet. Makes 48 biscuits.
Can be frozen raw for several weeks.
Take out and let rise and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Yield: 48 biscuits.

title: manana dip
directions: Layer beans, cheese, sour cream, tomato, onion and chiles. Repeat until ingredients are used up.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: eight layer taco dip
directions: In medium skillet, prepare taco spices and seasonings with ground beef and water according to package directions.
Add refried beans and heat 5 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water and cornstarch.
Stir until bubbly over medium heat. Sprinkle Jell-O and sweetener into mixture.
Stir well.
Cool. Add berries and put into a butter recipe graham cracker crust. Chill and add lite Cool Whip, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix cake mix and bake as directed in a 13 x 9-inch glass dish. Five minutes before taking from oven, bring pineapple, juice and sugar to a boil.
Pour on cake immediately as cake comes from oven. Let cool, then mix pudding and pour over cooled cake.
When pudding is set, ice with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with coconut and pecan pieces.
Cover and chill for 8 hours.
I think it's even better after a couple days.

title: kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut and put in mixing bowl.
Combine sugar and vinegar in saucepan and bring to boil.
Cook 5 minutes and cool slightly. Pour over kraut.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Sift flour before measuring.
Add spices.
Sift with soda or add soda in buttermilk. Add flour and milk alternately with creamed butter, sugar and eggs. Add jam.
Add floured pecans and chopped dates or raisins.
Pour into large tube pan, floured and lined with brown paper and well-greased.
Bake in oven at 325° to 350° for 1 hour or until done when tested with straw comes out clean.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef in skillet or cook ham bone. Combine all other ingredients in large kettle and cook for 1 hour. Add meat and keep warm until served. The tomato paste is very important. It makes soup much better.

title: sweet pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let marinate in refrigerator for 30 minutes or longer. When ready to serve, put on a bed of lettuce on a flat dish and garnish with small sweet pickles.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add beaten egg yolks.
Add molasses and brandy.
Sift flour, nutmeg, salt and baking powder. Add to mixture.
Add pecans and currants.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a loaf pan which has been greased and floured at 275° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Wrap in wine-soaked cloth for storage.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix pineapple with juice and blueberries. Sprinkle sugar on top. Spread cake mix on. Drizzle melted butter over mixture and add nuts. Cook at 350° for 40 minutes. After 25 minutes, punch holes in top so juice will come to the top.

title: sweet dough
directions: Scald milk (in microwave) and then put Crisco, sugar and salt into milk and dissolve.
Cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in the lukewarm water, then add to milk mixture, along with eggs.
Beat in flour.
Let rise until light or doubled, about 1 hour.
Knead well and shape into rolls.
Let rise again (1 hour).
Bake at 400° until golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Blend well all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Pour into pizza crust.
Will make two 12-inch pizzas or one 16-inch pizza.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix; pour into 4 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together; heat in pan.
Can be stored in refrigerator for a long time.

title: egg puff
directions: Mix all together in 1 bowl until well mixed together.
Put in oven at 375° for 30 minutes, or until light brown.

title: holiday apple salad
directions: Dissolve red hots in boiling water.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and cool until mixture thickens.
Fold in 1 cup chopped apples, pineapple and walnuts.
Chill until set.

title: white beans with tomato, basil and parmesan
directions: In a 12-inch nonstick skillet, heat the oil over low heat.
Add the garlic and cook, stirring occasionally for 4 minutes or until lightly colored and fragrant.
Stir in the beans, tomato and basil. Cook for about 7 minutes or until heated through.
Stir in the cheese and lemon juice.
Serve hot or at room temperature.
Serves 4 as a main dish, or 8 as a side dish.

title: waldori salad
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Over very low heat melt 1 cup peanut butter until smooth.
In top of double boiler, melt chocolate chips, butter and 1 cup peanut butter.
Place 1 tablespoon melted chocolate mixture in bottom of small paper muffin cups.
Then put 1 tablespoon peanut butter. Divide remaining chocolate mixture over top.
Makes 24.

title: beef burgundy stew
directions: Coat beef with flour; set aside. In 6-quart pot over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp. Remove with slotted spoon. Set aside.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Simmer ribs in salted water until tender.
Cut them into separate ribs.
Melt oleo in saucepan and add 1 clove crushed garlic.
Simmer 4 to 5 minutes.
Add ketchup, chili sauce, brown sugar, chopped onion, Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, celery seed, salt, pepper sauce and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil and pour over drained ribs in a roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, basting often.

title: new england skillet dinner
directions: Cook potatoes; peel and cut into 1/2-inch cubes and set aside. In a large skillet, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add carrots; cover and cook 10 minutes over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook until cabbage is tender.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add molasses and unbeaten egg.
Blend well.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with vinegar and water.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until brown.

title: rabbit stew
directions: Cut meat into 2-inch cubes.
Remove excess fat.
Brown in oil. Put rabbit in a large kettle.
Add wine, oil, tomatoes and vinegar.
Place spices in bag and remove before serving.
Add onions and cook slowly for 3 hours.
Add bouillon before serving.

title: ham raisin sauce
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Slowly add the remaining ingredients.
Stir over low heat until thick.
(Make just before serving.)
Good over baked ham.

title: no-bake peanut squares
directions: Combine corn syrup and brown sugar in a 3-quart pan.
Cook over moderate heat until it bubbles.
Stir.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, cereal and coconut.
Press into a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: uncooked peanut butter candy
directions: Add all ingredients together with little drops of milk until mixture is thick and mixed together well.
Then roll small parts by hand into balls and refrigerate until wanted.
Can be eaten right away.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Stir all but flour in a large nonmetal container until the yeast dissolves.
Stir in flour gradually until a smooth batter forms.
Let stand loosely covered in a warm place about 3 days, stirring down occasionally.
Refrigerate, loosely covered.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat milk, sugar and butter.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Pour over bread.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cornmeal and salt. Add butter, lemon juice, lemon rind and milk. Mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Yields one 9-inch pie. So-o-o delicious!

title: tex-mex layered dip
directions: On bottom of 2-quart glass casserole, spread refried beans. Mix sour cream with taco seasoning and spread on top of bean layer.
Next, layer picante sauce.
Mix avocados with lemon juice; layer on top of picante sauce.
Continue layering each of the remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Refrigerate and serve chilled with tortilla chips.
Serves 25.

title: sausage balls
directions: Cut cheese into cubes. Place in top of double boiler.
Cook over hot water, stirring frequently until melts. Place sausage, Bisquick and cheese in large mixing bowl. Mix well. Shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Freeze until firm.
Place in plastic bag.
Freeze.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: winter fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together.
Stir sugar and cornstarch together in saucepan.
Blend in 3/4 cup pineapple juice, lemon juice, orange peel and orange juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
While hot pour over fruit mixture.
Refrigerate uncovered several hours. Serves 12.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes and oleo in a large bowl.
Add salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cover with crushed cornflakes mixed with oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese-spinach appetizers
directions: Thaw spinach.
Squeeze moisture out between paper towels. Sift flour, salt and baking powder. Combine all ingredients by hand. Spread evenly into well buttered 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until brown.
Remove from oven.
Let set a few minutes and cut into pieces.

title: oatmeal chocolate chips
directions: Drop spoonfuls onto pan and bake at 350°.

title: never fail orange sherbet jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Fold in sherbet.
Let set until slightly thickened, about 20 minutes.
Fold in fruit.
Pour into mold and refrigerate overnight.

title: senator russell sweet potatoes
directions: Put ingredients into buttered casserole dish and bake about 45 minutes at about 350°.
Top with the following mixture:

title: peach supreme pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add melted butter. Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Lay halved peaches, flat side down, on bottom of unbaked pie shell. Spread mixture over peaches and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes one 8-inch pie.

title: no-bake fruitcake
directions: Stir evaporated milk, marshmallows, and orange juice concentrate in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat until marshmallows melt.
Take off heat and stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Press firmly into 5- or 6-cup ring mold or loaf pan lined with waxed paper.
Cover tightly.
Chill 2 days. Makes 3 pounds.

title: hobo bread
directions: Mix raisins, soda and water.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Pour into 3 well-greased pound coffee cans (2/3 full).
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: irish cream
directions: Add in order; mix well.
Put in bottle to cool.

title: mr. nik's ranch style chicken
directions: Boil chicken after removing skin.
Cool and pick meat off bones.
Mix 1 can tomatoes, 1 cup wine and mushroom soup.
Mix into chicken and bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cut seafood pieces in half.
Chop up celery also; rip up the leaves.
Add those to the salad.
Cut up onion real fine.
Cook eggs, then mash them; add to salad.
Mix all ingredients together. Now add Miracle Whip.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Best served cold. Serve with crackers.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Mix on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: steak with sour cream sauce(makes 6 servings)
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Coat meat with flour and score with a sharp knife.
Coat again with flour.
In skillet, melt butter; brown meat slowly on all sides. Combine tomatoes, green pepper and onion; pour over meat.
Cover and simmer over low heat 2 to 2 1/2 hours until meat is fork-tender.
Transfer meat to a warm platter.
Into liquid in skillet, blend 1 tablespoon flour; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Serve immediately over Spanish steak.

title: peanut butter crunchies
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in medium sized boiler.
Heat until creamy.
Remove and add peanut butter.
Stir thoroughly.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Sift together flour, cornmeal, soda, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Blend egg into the sour cream.
Stir in dry ingredients. Turn dough onto floured pastry cloth and knead lightly.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Brush with melted margarine.
Crease and fold over.
Sprinkle lightly with cornmeal.
Place on baking sheet and bake in 425° oven 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 rolls.

title: curried apple-tomato soup
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a 4 cup glass measure or microwave-proof bowl.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 4 to 6 minutes, or until heated through.

title: pumpkin cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 24 paper baking cups in muffin tins.
Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Mix remaining ingredients; add to dry ingredients.
Stir until dry ingredients are barely moistened.
Fill paper cups 2/3 full.
Bake about 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from muffin tins and cool on rack.
Freeze cupcakes that will not be eaten in the next four days.

title: uncooked peanut butter candy
directions: Mix all together with your hands.
Press mixture in greased dish.
Let set several hours, then cut into squares.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In large Dutch oven, saute in olive oil the onion, garlic, celery and celery tops.
Then add chopped chuck and cook until meat is browned.
Add water, salt, pepper, potatoes and carrots. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Finally add remaining vegetables and seasonings.
Mix together and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ham roll
directions: Spread each ham slice with a layer of cream cheese.
Roll each ham slice up, jelly roll fashion.
With sharp knife, cut rolls into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange on a serving platter and chill.

title: calico bean salad
directions: Toss beans with green pepper, relish and salami.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in water and vinegar; cook and stir until thickened.
Pour over bean mixture. Serves 4 or 5.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix chopped chicken, onion, celery, broth and soup well. After you mix this well, add your chow mein noodles.
Pour into casserole and bake about one hour at 300°.
(You can use any amount of chopped chicken you want, if you have leftover turkey it is also good to use.)

title: squash puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients, then add enough drained water from squash for consistency to drop with a teaspoon into deep fat to form puffs about the size of hushpuppies.
Yields 20 to 25 puffs.

title: swiss tuna-rice pie
directions: Combine rice and butter.
Stir in 1 egg and chopped olives. Spread evenly over bottom and sides of greased 9-inch pie pan to make a shell.
Gradually stir scalded milk into 2 slightly beaten eggs.
Add onion, salt, pepper and tuna.
Pour into rice-lined pie pan and sprinkle cheese over the top.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and bake additional 15 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, salt, oleo and milk in saucepan; boil 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto wax paper and let set.
My kid's favorite.

title: jodie's fruit dip
directions: Use mixer to blend.
Refrigerate.
Serve with apples, strawberries, etc.

title: chicken livers with bacon
directions: Wash
and
pat dry with paper towel the chicken livers. Cut each liver in half.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Wrap each piece of	liver
with
slice
of
bacon and secure with a toothpick.	Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Serve
hot.
Use as many chicken livers as needed for number you expect to serve.

title: glenda's grilled pork tenderloin
directions: Heat meat made at the market from strip of loin (backbone removed), containing 10 to 14 ribs.
Season with salt and pepper. Place in shallow baking dish, bone end up; wrap tips in foil to prevent excess browning.
Insert meat thermometer so tip is in center of thick part of loin.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and eggs.
Add rest and mix well.
Make a ball and flatten with a fork.
Bake on greased cookie sheet, approximately 12 to 15 minutes, at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together, then place in casserole dish. Crush 1 small bag of potato chips and place on top. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese quiche
directions: Sprinkle crumbled bacon onto precooked pie crust.
Combine broccoli and cheese with rest of the ingredients and mix well. Pour into crust and bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and green noodle casserole
directions: Melt cheese with soup and add sauteed vegetables (onion, green pepper and celery sauteed in 6 tablespoons margarine).
Combine all ingredients except onion rings.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with onion rings.

title: chocolate punch bowl trifle
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package instructions using a 9 x 13 pan. Cool completely on wire rack.

title: fresh turnip greens
directions: Remove and discard stems and any discolored spots from greens. Wash thoroughly and drain.
Tear into bite size pieces.
Set aside.
Combine olive oil and butter in a large stockpot.
Add garlic and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add greens; cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 35 to 45 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in salt and pepper.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Fold in thawed strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Pour half of this mixture into 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish and chill until firm.
Spread top with sour cream.
Gently spoon on rest of jello mixture.
Chill until firm.
Excellent dessert salad.
Serves 12.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Combine egg, pizza sauce, salt, pepper and corn flakes in a large bowl.
Mix well, until thoroughly combined.
Add ground beef, onion and mushrooms; then mix lightly.
Place 1/2 of meat mix evenly in bottom of 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan (ungreased).
Place 2 slices of cheese over meat mix.
Place remaining meat mix over cheese. Bake 1 hour in 350° oven or until meat begins to shrink from sides of pan.
Cut remaining cheese in narrow strips.
Remove loaf from oven and place strips diagonally over loaf.
Return to oven until cheese melts.
Cut into squares and serve hot.

title: smoke house spaghetti
directions: Saute bacon, add onion and hamburger.
Brown.
Stir in tomato sauce, pepper, garlic, salt and mushrooms with liquid.
Simmer. Cook 1/2 to 2/3 pound spaghetti.
Stir into sauce.
Layer spaghetti and cheese in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until hot. May be frozen.

title: hether's favorite chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the cream of mushroom, cream of celery and cream of chicken soups, Worcestershire sauce, poultry seasoning, Pepperidge Farm cornbread stuffing and butter or margarine.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo and put in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over top of melted oleo.
Do not mix.
Melt remaining stick of oleo and add 2 cups powdered sugar plus a little milk to consistency of thin frosting.
Add vanilla.
Pour over graham cracker crumbs, but do not mix in.
Add pineapple (drained) to make another layer.
Slice 4 or 5 bananas to make another layer.
Add Dream Whip.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Sliced strawberries may be added to garnish; chill.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into your ice cream freezer.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Make first stuffing mix as directed. Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole.
Add chicken, soup, milk and vegetables. Make other stuffing mix.
Put on top of other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for ribs
directions: Heat sugars, broth and water until sugar is melted.
Add remaining ingredients, except ribs, and simmer 2 hours.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Slice and boil carrots in salted water until fork-tender. Cool.
Alternate layers of carrots, pepper rings and onion slices (thin).

title: texas casserole
directions: Brown meat; pour off fat.
Add garlic juice and butter.
Saute 20 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and sugar, salt and pepper to taste. Simmer 15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream and chopped onions.
While noodles are cooking according to package directions, alternate layers of noodles, meat mixture and cheese mixture in a 3-quart dish.
Repeat twice.
Top with mushroom soup.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Add grated cheese during the last 5 minutes of cooking time.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup in saucepan to medium crack (280°).
Add salt and extract.
Pour over popcorn in large bowl sprayed with Pam.
Shape into balls.
Makes 12 balls.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in carrots.
Pour into pan (tube, Bundt, etc.).
Bake at 350° until cake springs back in center.
Use cream cheese icing.

title: fish dijon
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Mix butter, mustard, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce. Spread over fish.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: broccoli soup with potato and cheddar cheese
directions: Heat oil
in
large
heavy
bottom
pot.
Add broccoli, potato, leek
and shallots and saute, stirring frequently over medium heat for
5	minutes.
Add
1 cup stock, thyme, oregano and curry.
Cover,
simmer
until
vegetables are very tender, about 30	minutes.
Stir	occasionally.
Let
soup cool.	Pour into blender or	food processor with mustard.
Process until a smooth puree (don't overpuree or potato will be gummy).
Pour puree
back into
pot.
Add remaining stock, milk and cheese. Heat
slowly, stirring
to blend well.
When cheese is melted it's ready.
Makes 1 quart.

title: crispy fried oven cooked chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Apply salt, pepper or other seasoning to chicken.
Roll chicken in flour, then dip in egg batter.
Brown each piece of chicken in hot skillet, then place chicken on broiler pan and place in 350° oven for 1 hour (uncovered).

title: pasta and ham salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until well blended.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix ingredients together except chocolate chips.
Spread out into oblong or square pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on top of mixture.
Let chill for 1 hour.

title: hamburger macaroni stuff
directions: Boil macaroni; drain and set aside.
Brown beef and onion; drain excess fat and set aside.
In a large pot, combine meat, cooked macaroni, beans and cheese packet.
Add butter and milk for cheese.
Heat thoroughly and serve.
Bock children's favorite lunch.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add 2 beaten eggs, syrup, oats, coconut, salt and vanilla.
Mix all together, pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: tony pizza
directions: Flatten one biscuit on a pan, then put pizza sauce on it, then add cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 325° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and hot water together until hard crack stage.
(When first begins to heat, stir gently until sugar dissolves and syrup is clear.)

title: chicken and stuffing casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water with a chicken bouillon cube. Take chicken off bones when cool and break in little pieces.
Put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Over this pour 3 cups of medium white sauce.
Make your own stuffing or use Stove Top stuffing (make stuffing).
Put stuffing on top of chicken and bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In a large glass bowl, sift cocoa and sugar together.
Place butter on top; add milk.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir and add nuts.
Microwave 45 seconds.
Spread in a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Do not cut until bottom of pan is cool.

title: frozen margarita pie
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in finely crushed pretzels and sugar.
Mix well. Press pretzel mixture on bottom and sides of a buttered 9 inch pie plate.

Chill. In a medium sized bowl, combine the remaining ingredients except the whipping cream. Blend well. Fold in whipped cream. Spoon onto crust. Freeze until well firmed (at least 4 hours). Garnish with lime twists.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water for about 3 minutes, then drain. Brown the beef and the onion; drain.
Combine all ingredients, except 3 tablespoons of the cheese.
Pour mixture into casserole dish; top with the reserved cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt the chips and oleo together.
Add powdered sugar, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Bring to boil for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: mint punch
directions: Boil water and sugar for 10 minutes.
Put remaining ingredients in crock or mixing bowl.
Pour hot syrup over the mixture and let stand at least 1 hour.
To serve, mix 1 part mixture, 2 parts water and 1 part ginger ale.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: green chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken; cool and remove meat from bones.
Spread cream of chicken soup over corn tortillas.
In a large casserole dish, lightly grease sides and bottom.
Start with pieces of chicken on bottom, then continue to layer all ingredients, ending with tortillas.
(Layers:
chicken, onions, jalapenos, cheese and tortillas; repeat.)
This makes several layers.
Once layers are complete, pour excess soup over the top.
Grate Cheddar cheese to cover the top.
Bake at 375°.
If baked same day, 30 to 45 minutes. If refrigerated and then baked, bake 1 hour.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl and mix with fork.
Form 2 balls and flatten with hands.
Roll out in wax paper.
Peel off and put into pie dish.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pie shells.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together. Sift flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder together. Add flour mixture to oil mixture. Then add vanilla and nuts. Divide into 2 greased pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Add sour cream, cream cheese, butter or margarine, onion salt and pepper to mashed potatoes.
Gradually beat in enough of the milk to make smooth and fluffy.
Spoon into a
greased 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Cover and chill up to 24 hours.
Dot with margarine and cook, covered, on High power for 8 to 10 minutes or until heated, stirring once.

title: marinated leg of lamb
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over lamb.
Turn from time to time, for about 2 hours or more.
Roast in 325° oven for 25 minutes to the pound or internal meat thermometer at 175° to 180° for well done; 160° to 165° for slightly pink (very tender).
Baste once or twice with marinade.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour 350 in 2 medium loaf pans.

title: curry chicken
directions: Put flour, salt and pepper in a paper bag.
Shake chicken in bag until coated.
Heat 4 tablespoons of butter in a large pot. Brown the chicken.
Add more butter as you need it.
Remove chicken; add onion, green pepper, garlic, curry powder and thyme. Cook five minutes.
Add tomatoes with the liquid from the can. Add chicken; cook, covered, 20 to 30 minutes.
Add currants to the chicken and stir.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Cook sauce with added ingredients:
meat, pineapple, bell pepper and onion.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: hamburger cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion.
Add ground chuck and brown; drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, chopped tomatoes and salt to taste. Add a cup of water and stir into the mixture about half of the cheese.
Add cooked noodles to mixture.
Stir, and when cheese is melted, pour into casserole dish.
Grate the remaining cheese and sprinkle on top.
Place in a 350° oven for 15 or 20 minutes until cheese is melted on top.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken with salt and pepper until done; save broth.
Add soups, tomatoes and 1 cup broth to deboned chicken.
Boil spaghetti in remaining broth, then mix chicken mixture and spaghetti together.
Add seasoning and more broth, if needed. Simmer until heated through.
Serve as is, or put in baking dish with Velveeta cheese on top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening; add buttermilk. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix altogether until moist.
Cover bowl and let sit at least 2 hours or overnight.
Use as needed. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or longer.

title: chocolate goop
directions: Blend the cream cheese into one of the small Cool Whips (or 1/2 of the large).
Follow the package directions to prepare chocolate pudding.
Layer cream cheese mixture into bottom of pie shell.
Add chocolate pudding.
Top with plain Cool Whip.
(If there's room, layer cream cheese mixture, pudding and Cool Whip again.)
Chill and serve.

title: cold meat sauce
directions: Blend well and serve with cold meat.
Great for leftovers, ham, beef or lamb.
Serve on a bed of lettuce, tomatoes, etc., and hot crusty bread or rolls.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
