directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup of boiling water, then add 1/2 cup cold water.
When mixture begins to jell, add cranberry sauce, orange, pineapple and walnuts.
Pour into sprayed mold and chill several hours.

title: crescent veggie appetizer tree
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove dough from cans in rolled sections (two sections from each can); do not unroll.
Cut each section into 8 slices (16 slices from each can).
Place slices, cut side down, on ungreased cookie sheets to form two trees.
To form each tree, start by placing 1 slice for top; arrange 2 slices just below, with sides touching.
Continue arranging in a row of 3 slices, then a new row of 4 slices, ending with a row of 5 slices.
Use remaining slice for trunk.
Refrigerate one tree.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until done; cool and peel them.
Grate potatoes and stir in sour cream and 1/2 of the cheese and the onions, salt and pepper.
Mix in a large bowl.
Put in a buttered dish and top with rest of cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika; cover. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and serve.

title: good pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Bake in ungreased cake pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Discard tamale wrapper.
Line tamales in casserole dish. Cover with chili.
Cover with lettuce.
Completely cover with cheese. Bake in preheated 325° oven for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly. Serve with nachos.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar 20 minutes.
Place a few peaches at a time in syrup.
Cook until tender.
Pack into sterilized jars. When jars are full, fill with juice to cover.
Seal jars immediately.

title: orange pineapple congeal
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Add jello and stir until dissolved. Cool.
Add buttermilk. Fold in topping and nuts.
Refrigerate until set.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Knead together until thoroughly blended.
Add reserved liquid if mixture is dry. Shake mixture into cakes approximately 2-inches in diameter. Place in nonstick skillet and brown on both sides.

title: lemon fruit dip
directions: Beat cottage cheese on high speed of mixer until smooth, about 5 minutes.
Stir in yogurt and lemon peel.
Garnish with a little strawberry, orange slice and watermelon wedge.
Serve with remaining fruit as dippers.
Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: oreo cookie dirt
directions: Freeze cookies and grind them in food processor until mixture looks like dirt.
Combine softened cream cheese, pudding, milk and whipped topping; beat until smooth, about 3 minutes.
Put a layer of cookie mixture in bottom of a new, sterilized flowerpot.
Add layer of pudding mixture.
Repeat layers as often as needed, ending with layer of cookie mixture.
Chill 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix together pretzels, margarine and 5 tablespoons sugar.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400° in 9 x 12-inch dish.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding mix with milk.
Beat until smooth and thick.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Add salt.
Pour over vanilla wafers and bananas.
Keep refrigerated.
Keeps longer than ordinary banana pudding.

title: creative chef one dish
directions: In a 2 qt. baking dish, mix soup, water, rice and paprika. Place chicken on rice mixture.
Sprinkle with additional paprika. Cover.
Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes or until chicken and rice are done.
Serves four.

title: brownies
directions: Beat oleo and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs (2 at a time). Add vanilla.
Stir in chocolate syrup.
Add nuts.
Bake in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine, 1 tsp cinnamon, 3/4 can Mt. Dew. Pour over dumplings and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or more depending on oven.

title: cherry slices
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°, then cool.

title: bachelor's heaven
directions: If full flavored sauerkraut is desired, combine all ingredients in a crock-pot or Dutch oven, using sauerkraut juice. Fill with water; put on low heat in the morning before going to work.
Eat in evening as a whole meal, preferably in a large, warmed soup dish with sauce, hot rolls and butter.
Save uneaten portion in the refrigerator and serve a second and third day.
It improves with age.

title: nanni's frizzini
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with sugar and salt.
Add beaten eggs, melted shortening and flour.
Knead and place in greased bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and let rise until doubled.
Dump out and divide into 24 rolls.
Roll in hands and push finger in center and stretch out to form doughnut shape.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake in 400° oven until light brown, about 15 minutes. Let cool, then cut in half, using a fork so center will be rough. Toast in oven at about 350° until dry.
Eat plain or buttered. (Can be left hot toasted, if desired.)

title: veal chops with raspberry vinegar(serves 2 to 4)
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
Brown in butter or oil. Cook about 5 minutes on each side.
Add garlic, bay leaf and thyme.
Cook 3 minutes.
Pour vinegar and broth around chops. Cover loosely and simmer 15 minutes or until chops are done. Remove garlic cloves.
Mash into a paste and blend into juices. Cover tightly and cook 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: chicken chop suey
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until slightly brown; add 1 cup water.
Simmer mixture for 20 minutes.
Add bean sprouts, chicken, mushrooms, brown sauce and soy sauce.
Mix cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water; stir into bean sprout mixture.
Simmer for 20 minutes longer.
Serve over cooked rice.
Sprinkle chow mein noodles over top for garnish.
Yields 8 servings.

title: pacific lime mold
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add juice from pineapple.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat until frothy. Fold in pineapple, cottage cheese, horseradish, mayonnaise and chopped nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: bread pudding
directions: Crumble bread.
Add milk until bread is crumbled under milk. Pour 1 cup sugar and vanilla on and let sit for 30 minutes.
Add melted butter.
Pour in and stir.
Put on stove for 30 minutes. Pour out in pan and let bake until it's brown.

title: rich spinach casserole
directions: In a 3-qt. slow cooker, combine all ingredients; mix well. Cover and cook on low for 2-1/2 hours or until the cheese is melted.

title: yummy sausage balls(servings:  4)
directions: Mix sausage and Bisquick.
Slit and deseed jalapenos.
Stuff with cheese.
Pinch closed.
Pinch off sausage.
Make a little pancake approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Wrap around pepper; roll around like an egg.
Dip "arm" egg in 1 beaten egg.
Roll in Shake 'n Bake mix.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 25 to 30 minutes on a greased pan (cookie sheet).

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs until light, then beat in sugar and soft shortening. Add large, ripe bananas; mash.
Sift in flour, salt and 1 teaspoon baking powder.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: breakfast cookies(healthy - no sugar!)
directions: Mash bananas.
Add remaining ingredients; beat well.
Let stand for a few minutes.
Drop from spoon onto lightly oiled cookie sheet, or spread over sheet and score into bars.
Bake for approximately 25 minutes at 350°, or until nicely browned.
Loosen with spatula immediately; let cool on cookie sheet.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Drain yams and mash. Add mayonnaise, dash of salt, pepper to taste, chopped onion, drained olives and sweet hot mustard. Prepare as you would regular potato salad. Add the chopped boiled eggs.

title: 5 p.m. news 3 beer meat loaf
directions: Open first beer and check kitchen for ingredients.
After all ingredients are accounted for, sit down and finish beer.
Open 2nd beer.
Mix beef, egg, milk, bread crumbs, finely chopped onions, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Throw the whole mess in a loaf pan and finish 2nd beer.
Form beef into loaf shape.
Open 3rd beer.
Place meat loaf in oven at 350°.
Turn on TV.
Watch the news and bake until brown or the news is over.
Finish 3rd beer.
Cover top of meat loaf with catsup and French fried onions and bake for 15 more minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Form into bite size balls; freeze for at least 2 days.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve while warm.

title: garlic crisps
directions: Cut tortillas into quarters. Coat with cooking spray and sprinkle with garlic salt. Place on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until golden. Cool. Store in an airtight container. Yield: 16 crisps.

title: eggplant parmesan deluxe
directions: Peel and cut eggplant in 1/2-inch crosswise slices.
Beat egg and milk.

Dip eggplant slices in mixture, then into bread crumbs. Saute a few slices in the oil until golden brown and fork tender. Over bottom of a greased 2-quart casserole, layer 1/2 of eggplant slices, 1/2 of tomato sauce, 1/2 of seasonings and 1/2 of cheeses. Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each egg.
Sift flour and add alternately with orange juice and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour in 250° to 300° oven.

title: broiled tomatoes
directions: Preheat broiler. Wash tomatoes. Cut out stem ends and cut in half crosswise. Sprinkle cut surface of each tomato with small amount of hot sauce, salt, pepper and sugar. Dot with butter. Place in broiler 4-inches from source of heat.
Broil for 10 to 12 minutes.
Combine small amount of butter with Parmesan cheese and crumbs.
Sprinkle tomato halves with crumb mixture during the last 3 minutes of broiling time. Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water in a gallon jar according to package directions.
Add pineapple juice.
Just before serving, add Sprite or 7-Up and stir well.

title: apple spice custard cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs; stir in apples.
Pour into well greased and floured 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: potato puffs
directions: Mix together the first 5 items and 2 tablespoons of the flour and refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape mixture into small balls, roll in remaining flour, dip in egg, then roll in dry bread crumbs.
Put balls on buttered cookie sheet and bake 25 minutes at 425°.
Makes 12 to 15 balls.

title: redskin potato salad
directions: Wash and cook potatoes with skins on.
Fry bacon crisp.
Slice onion into thin rings.
Layer slices of potatoes, layer of green beans, onions, crumbled bacon, dash of Italian dressing in a sealable bowl.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used. Seal bowl and refrigerate.
Turn upside down to distribute dressing.
Prepare the day before.

title: crisp pickle slices
directions: Do not peel cucumbers.
Slice thin.
Add onions, peppers and whole garlic cloves.
Add salt; cover with cracked ice.
Mix thoroughly.
Leave in salt 3 hours.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over cucumbers.
Heat jars to boiling point and seal.

title: vegetable crunch
directions: Cook cauliflower and carrots in boiling water for 8 minutes. Add peas and cook for 4 minutes.
Drain and keep warm.
Melt margarine in a pan; remove from heat and stir in flour.
Blend in the milk and salt and pepper.
Return to boil, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cook for 2 minutes, then mix in half of the cheese and cooked vegetables.
Turn into large ovenproof dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs, remaining cheese and sesame seed.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes until golden brown.

title: tamale pie
directions: In skillet melt 1 tablespoon shortening, brown meat, onion and seasonings, crumbling meat into small pieces.
Cook until done. Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in a skillet until brown. Drain fat. Set aside. In a medium saucepan, combine tomato sauce, cheese, oregano, basil and ground beef (cooked). Stir over medium heat until outer edge begins to bubble. Serve over favorite pasta noodles.

title: broccoli and mushroom quiche(makes 2 quiches)]
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Fold in cream, cheese and then remaining ingredients.
Fill pie shells with the mixture.
Top with a little of the reserved shredded cheese you have put aside. Bake in preheated oven at 425° for about 45 minutes or until done. Can be frozen.

title: dilly's meatballs
directions: Mix first four ingredients, shape into meatballs and brown. Drain and add mushroom soup and water. Simmer for 15 minutes. Remove from heat, mix in sour cream. Serve warm.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat until fluffy.
Add flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour salt and pepper.
Roll meat in flour and lightly brown in hot oil for 2 minutes on each side.
Place in baking pan. Place onions and carrots over meat.
Cover with gravy and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water; add orange juice and stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple and drained mandarin oranges.
Place in refrigerator and let congeal.

title: swiss potato soup
directions: Cook soup according to directions on the box.
Add cubed potatoes and cook until potatoes are done.
Add cream of potato soup and 3 soup cans of milk to onion soup and heat.
Add chopped onion and grated Swiss cheese to hot soup.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Sour cream may be added at this time.
Stir thoroughly. Heat a few minutes longer and serve.

title: mock duck
directions: Mix bread crumbs with parsley, butter, salt and pepper.
Put dressing in center of steak.
Roll steak; tie securely.
Put 2 large tablespoons shortening in skillet and brown on both sides of roll.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes and water. Cover and let simmer in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: skillet cherry chicken
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients. Set aside.
Combine flour and salt in paper or plastic bag. Add 2 or 3 pieces of chicken at a time and shake.
Brown chicken in oil over medium heat, turning with tongs.
Cover and cook 15 minutes. Drain off fat.
Add cherry sauce. Cover and simmer over very low heat, skin side up for 15 minutes. Turn and simmer 15 minutes more or until tender.

title: sausage and mushroom stew
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven or casserole, combine all ingredients except cabbage.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and stir. Add the cabbage. Cover and bake 30 to 45 minutes longer at 350° or until vegetables are tender. Stir before serving. Serves 6.

title: banana muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin pan with margarine or use foil muffin papers.
Mix flours, wheat germ, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking powder, baking sodas and salt; set aside.
In electric mixer, mix oil and brown sugar.
Add egg and vanilla and mix well. Add mashed bananas and blend until smooth.
Mix in flour mixture. Fold in nuts.
Bake muffins for 30 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Serves 16.

title: 2-step chicken broccoli divan
directions: In 9-inch shallow casserole, arrange broccoli; top with chicken.
Combine soup and milk; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine butter and bread crumbs; sprinkle over cheese.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Saute celery, onions and green pepper in small amount of margarine for about 25 minutes.
Stir in soups, Chinese vegetables, salt and pepper.
Heat.
Stir in chow mein noodles.
Save some noodles.
Put in casserole in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle remaining noodles on top and return to oven for 15 minutes.

title: mark's mcfamous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir together butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs; mix well. Gradually add flour and salt, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate chips and mix.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: impossible blt pie recipe
directions: Grease 10-inch pie plate. Layer bacon and cheese in plate. Beat remaining ingredients except lettuce and tomatoes until smooth. Pour into plate. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 400°. Cool 5 minutes. Garnish with lettuce, tomatoes and crumbled bacon.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Mix ingredients in bowl until smooth.
Place into prepared bread pan.
Bake for 1-1/2 hours. This is a heavy bread and is like sour dough bread.
The beer is used for yeast.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: hot milk cake(delicious with fruit)
directions: Add sugar to well beaten eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture.
Heat milk and butter.
Add to mix and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a greased and floured 8-inch square pan.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes. Mix all together. Lightly oil or spray 13 x 9 pan. Spread mixture into pan. Sprinkle dried bread crumbs over top. Bake 1 hour at 350°. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: marvelous apple-n-cranberry cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs together.
Combine dry ingredients; stir into oil mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well (dough will be stiff).
Pour into lightly greased Bundt pan and bake at 325° for an hour.
Delicious.

title: hot dip
directions: Cook ground beef and drain off fat.
Pour in cheese soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Heat until hot.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: ratatouille
directions: Saute onions in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Add peppers, zucchini and squash.
Cook until half done.
Add tomatoes and seasoning. Cook until desired tenderness.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Cover the potatoes with water plus about 1-inch in large Dutch oven. Add onion and salt to taste while cooking. Cook onion and potatoes until tender.
Cube the cream cheese and add to potatoes and onions. Stir until melted.
Add soup, garlic salt and milk to desired consistency. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Set oven for 375 degrees and lightly grease cookie sheet. Sift flour once, measure, add baking powder, soda and salt. Sift again.
Mix sugars, shortening, egg and peanut butter in mixing bowl.
Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill dough. Roll balls about the size of a quarter and place on cookie sheet. Flatten the balls with a fork dipped in flour making a crisscross design.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: lo-cal beef stroganoff(diabetic recipe)
directions: Heat butter and oil in heavy skillet.
Saute meat and onion until meat loses its redness.
Mix the bouillon cube and cornstarch in water.
Add this mixture and remaining ingredients, except yogurt, to the meat and simmer about 1 hour until meat is tender. Stir in yogurt and heat thoroughly.
Serve over hot rice, if desired.
Makes 4 (3/4 cup) servings.
Each serving equals 1/2 low-fat milk, 3 lean meat and 2 fat exchanges.
Each serving contains 285 calories.

title: cherry dream squares
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease 13 x 9 pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1 cup rolled oats. Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs, add 1 egg; mix well.
Press into prepared pan and pour cherry pie filling over crust; spread to cover.
To reserved crumbs, in a large bowl, add remaining 1/4 cup rolled oats, 2 tablespoons margarine, nuts and brown sugar.
Beat until well mixed.
Sprinkle over cherry mixture.
Bake 30 - 40 minutes.
Cool completely.
Makes 12 servings.

title: persimmon pudding(heritage)
directions: Mix ingredients in a large mixing bowl.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut off tips of corn kernels into a large bowl.
Add salt and pepper.
Sprinkle flour over the corn and mix well.
Set aside. Chop peppers and set aside.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Heat oil enough to cover bottom of a 10-inch skillet.
Add the butter and margarine and melt over medium heat.
Add corn; stir.

title: unboiled custard
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and then fold in Cool Whip.
Use in place of egg nog.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Beat egg yolks well and combine with

potatoes, sugar, milk and cinnamon. Beat egg whites until stiff and mix them in the potato mixture. Combine, oats, brown sugar, pecans and melted margarine. Sprinkle over top of potatoes. Bake at 350° or 400° oven for 55 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: hawaiian dessert
directions: Mix cake batter according to package.
Pour into 2 greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until cakes test done.
Cool completely.
In a large mixing bowl, combine pudding mixes, milk and coconut extract, beat for 2 minutes.
Add the cream cheese and beat well.
Stir in pineapple.
Spread over cooled cakes.
Top with whipped cream, sprinkle with toasted coconut. Chill 2 hours.
Prepared dessert can be covered and frozen for up to 1 month.

title: rice hawaiian
directions: Combine pineapple, lemon juice, sugar and salt and fold into whipped cream.
Fold in rice and coconut.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill before serving.
Serves 6.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add ice cream, juice from raspberries and lemonade.
Let thicken and add 1 cup chopped nuts and raspberries.
Let congeal.

title: one pan chicken and noodles
directions: Combine all, except for chicken and noodles, in a deep skillet on top of stove.
Stir until combined and starting to boil.
Add chicken and noodles, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: peach bavarian cream
directions: Combine peaches, lemon juice and salt.
Let stand 1 hour. Soften gelatin in water, then dissolve over low heat.
Combine with peach mixture and chill.
When mixture begins to thicken, fold in whipped cream.
Place in individual molds and chill until firm.
Serve with peach slice or whipped cream on top.

title: low cholesterol chicken madeira
directions: Mix bread crumbs with garlic powder and rosemary.
Dip the chicken in egg white and roll in seasoned bread crumbs.
Brown both sides of chicken under the broiler.
Place in a shallow baking dish.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a Bundt pan.

title: coconut pineapple cake
directions: Mix together and place in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Sift together dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk to dry mixture.
Knead dough until it holds together; roll dough to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter and fold in half. Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Dough may be refrigerated or frozen for later use.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: cloppino(chi pee no)
directions: Saute all veggies and garlic in oil.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, basil, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 2 hours.

title: mexican corn bread sticks
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients into a medium bowl. Make a well in the center of mixture. Combine buttermilk and next 3 ingredients. Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Fold in cheese. Spoon into a muffin pan or a corn stick pan, filling about 2/3 way full. Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Makes about 16 sticks.

title: rosettes
directions: Add sugar to slightly beaten eggs, then add milk.
Sift flour before measuring, then combined flour and salt.
Stir in first mixture until batter is smooth and about the consistency of
heavy cream.
Add
flavoring.
Dip iron into hot fat in a deep kettle to heat it.
Drain excess fat on brown paper.
Fat should
be
hot enough to brown a piece of bread, counting to 60.
Dip
heated iron in batter, not more than 3/4 its height. If only
a
thin layer
of batter adheres to the iron, dip it again until smooth layer forms.
It will be partly cooked from the
heat of the iron. Plunge batter-coated iron quickly into the hot
fat
and
cook, from
2 to 3 minutes or until active bubbling ceases.
Remove from iron and drain on brown paper or paper towels.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes. Boil until very tender. Drain. Mash potatoes and season with salt and pepper. Add cheese and bacon bits. Stir until combined. Add milk until desired thickness is achieved. Stir in scallions. Heat through and serve.

title: fish fillets(serves 1)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In small mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except fish.
Place fish on foil and spread mixture over fish.
Wrap tightly and bake for 30 minutes.

title: green and gold rice casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until soft.
Add soup, cheese and garlic powder.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Add mushrooms (undrained), broccoli and rice.
Turn into buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with French fried onions or cornbread stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Saute onion in a little oil or margarine.
Add ground beef, brown well and drain.
Add chopped cabbage and water.
Simmer until cabbage is tender.
Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients. Simmer until well heated, stirring once or twice.
Other spices, such as oregano and basil, may be added.
Serve over rice.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Combine pineapple with juice with sour cream and prepared vanilla pudding.
Mix well and pour into crust.
Frost with thawed Cool Whip and refrigerate.
Tastes best when refrigerated overnight.

title: rainbow bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain and put into soup pot with garlic and water or stock.
Bring to boil; simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots; simmer 1 more hour.
Add tomatoes, onions, green pepper, parsley, lime juice and chili powder.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Stir in cilantro and salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 8.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter together. Pour over Rice Chex.
Pour powdered sugar onto Rice Chex until they are all coated.

title: hot punch
directions: Mix sugar, water and juices.
Bring to a boil.	Drop in tea tied in cloth and let stand for 1 minute before serving.

title: winter fruit bowl
directions: Pare and section the grapefruit.
Reserve the juice.
Set the sections aside.
To any juice from the grapefruit, add water to make one cup.
Combine sugar and marmalade.
Heat to boiling, making certain sugar dissolves.
Add cranberries, stirring until you hear the skins pop, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add grapefruit sections; cover and chill.
Just before serving, slice bananas and stir into grapefruit mixture.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Stir in sauce mix and water.
Heat to boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, until slightly thickened, about 10 minutes.
Cook pasta in 6 cups water until tender, 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain.
Heat oven to 375°.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Cook on low heat.
Add meatballs, heat through.
Serve over noodles and top with sour cream to taste.

title: southwest white chili
directions: Heat oil in 3-quart saucepan over medium-high heat. Add chicken.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes stirring often.
Remove chicken with slotted spoon. Cover and keep warm.
Add chopped onion to saucepan and cook until onion is clear.
Stir in chicken broth, green chilies, garlic powder, ground cumin, oregano leaves and red pepper. Simmer 20 minutes.
Garnish with cheese and onions.
This dish is low-fat.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli just until tender and drain.
Mix all but 3/4 cup cheese and bread crumbs together.
Add to drained broccoli. Place in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and the last 3/4 cup grated cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°, covered.
Bake last 10 minutes, uncovered.
(Can be made one day and baked the next.) Serves 10 to 12.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix together soup and milk.
Layer potatoes, onion and margarine in big bowl.
Sprinkle each layer with flour and salt and pepper.
Pour soup over everything.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: apple cranberry crisp
directions: Peel apples and slice thin.
Arrange in square baking dish about 10 x 6-inch.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Spoon cranberry sauce over this.
Stir rolled oats (oatmeal), flour and brown sugar together.
Cut in butter until evenly mixed and crumbled. Sprinkle this over cranberry layer.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until apples are cooked through and top is lightly browned, about 40 minutes.
Good served plain or with whipped cream of vanilla ice cream.
Serve hot.
Serves 8.

title: hamburgers in sauce
directions: Fry some hamburgers and add to the sauce.
Fill the chili sauce jar with water and then add the mustard and brown sugar. You can add some onions if you desire.
Simmer.

title: cream biscuits (baking powder)
directions: Combine flour and cream in a bowl with a fork, mixing just until flour is moist (the dough is too sticky to handle).
Place 1/4 cup flour in another bowl.
Drop approximately 2 tablespoons of dough into the flour; roll around until lightly coated.
Take out and pat into a disc, about 1/2-inch thick.
Place on ungreased pan.
Let the biscuits rest for 5 minutes.
Place in center of preheated 450° oven and bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 6 biscuits; 230 calories each.

title: fruity bran muffins
directions: Mix bran and juice.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in Egg Beaters, margarine and fruit spread.
Mix flour and baking powder. Stir into bran mixture until just blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Spoon into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: asheville salad
directions: Bring tomato soup to boiling point.
Add cream cheese.
Stir until smooth.
Add gelatin which has been softened in cold water. Let partly cool.
Add mayonnaise and chopped celery.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Mix together margarine, brown sugar and eggs; add flour and nuts.
Save
cups
of this mixture.
Pat remaining mixture in	9
x 13-inch pan.
Spread preserves on this crust, leaving 1/2-inch
around edge.
Take the reserved mixture and crumble over preserves.	Bake
at
350°	for 25 to 30 minutes. After cooled, melt almond bark and drizzle over top.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths.
Shake biscuits in a bag with sugar and cinnamon.
Layer biscuits into greased tube pan (not with removable bottom).
Sprinkle chopped nuts between layers, if desired.
Melt the brown sugar and butter and boil for 1 minute. Pour over biscuits.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before removing from pan.
To serve, just pinch off a piece and eat with fingers.

title: creme a rhum
directions: Combine in a double boiler the sugar, fruit juices, egg yolks, wine and rum.
Place over heat and beat continuously with an eggbeater until foamy and thickened.
Remove from the heat and add the gelatin which has been softened in the cold water.
Cool until it is syrupy.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Pour into a well-oiled quart mold and chill for at least 3 hours.
Serve with small dish of whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: elegant carrots
directions: Cook carrots to tender, approximately 8 minutes.
Turn carrots into baking dish.
Stir in raisins, margarine, honey, lemon juice and ginger.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Spoon into serving dishes.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Serve.

title: cheddar cheese ring
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and put into 3 1/2 ring mold; chill. Invert cheese ball on plate.
Fill center with strawberry preserves. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: communion wafers
directions: Sift flour and salt again.
Blend oil and cold water.
Pour over flour and mix into soft ball.
Knead a few minutes.
Roll out thin.
Mark off with a dull knife into 3/4-inch squares.
Bake in moderate oven until golden brown.

title: cathy's chocolate delight dessert
directions: Mix butter, flour and 1/2 cup of the walnuts. Press into the bottom of the pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until light brown. Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar until blended. Spread on top of cooled crust. Mix chocolate pudding mix with milk. Spread on top of Cool Whip/cream cheese layer. Spread another container of Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle remainder of walnuts and flakes of Hershey bar on top.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and marinate in refrigerator for 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix
ingredients together, stirring well.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell and bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: summer vegetable sauce
directions: Saute garlic and pepper in olive oil until garlic begins to turn golden.
Remove and discard.
Add the cooked vegetables and continue cooking until pasta is done.
Add drained pasta to vegetables.
Toss while over heat for a moment or two; remove from heat and serve.

title: famous oatmeal cookies(yields 5 dozen)
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla together until creamy.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture and blend well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mom's company beef casserole
directions: Boil noodles; drain and rinse.	Brown meat lightly.
Add tomato sauce and set aside.
Mix cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onion and bell pepper with electric mixer until smooth.
Put 2/3 of noodles in 2 1/2 quart casserole.
Add all of cheese mixture (layer on top).
Add rest of noodles and meat (layer over top).
Cover and chill overnight.
Cook 1 hour at 375°, covered.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Grease a large casserole dish with butter.
Brown meat, onion and seasonings; drain. Add enchilada sauce.
In a separate pan, heat soup, water and green chilies.
Line bottom and sides of prepared dish with tortillas.
Layer meat, soup mixture, cheese and tortillas until all mixture is used.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour in a 2-quart bowl or pan.

title: lentil soup
directions: Boil lentils and rice in water.
When starts boiling, reduce heat.
Cover and let cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Then blend in blender; return to heat.
Add salt, pepper and cumin.
Fry onion in oil separate, until golden brown, then add to lentil.
Cook for 10 minutes together.
Garnish with parsley.
Eat it warm.
Makes enough for 4 people.

title: okra delight
directions: Place vegetables in bowl.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Add to vegetables.
Thoroughly coat vegetables.
Drain off excess fluids. Place corn meal and flour in paper bag.
Add vegetables.
Shake well to coat.
Deep fat fry to a golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend in blender until ice is fine.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch pan; brush up onto sides of pan. Add brown sugar; blend over low heat.
Remove from heat and arrange pineapple halves and cherries.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat cake mix, eggs, oranges and juice and margarine together for 3 minutes.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and top with Mandarin Orange Frosting.

title: applesauce (pear or peach) oatmeal bread(recipe for bread maker machine)
directions: Set machine on "mix" setting if you have one (seems to do best).

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Mix together butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla until creamy. Alternately add dry ingredients to creamy mixture.
Last stir in oats and morsels.

title: hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Combine cheese, soup and remaining ingredients, except biscuits, in a casserole.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Place biscuits around edge.
Return to oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: easy italian beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for at least 1 hour or more.
Serve on hard rolls.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Stir together.
Make meatballs and brown in 1 Tbsp. butter. Mix 20 oz. bottle of tangy Brooks catsup and 1 (10 oz.) jar apple or currant jelly.
Stir and pour over meatballs.
Let simmer for 25 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Fold in pecans.
Bake at 350° for one hour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: layered salad
directions: Break or cut lettuce and place in bottom of a large bowl. Add a layer of green onions.
Add a layer of celery slices.
Add a layer of cauliflower pieces.
Add cooked bacon pieces.
Add shredded cheese.
Cover with Miracle Whip to seal it completely. Let it set for several hours or overnight.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine Crisco, salt and peanut butter; mix well.
Gradually add sugar and brown sugar.
Cream thoroughly after each addition. Add eggs and milk, mixing well.
Sift together the flour and soda, blend with first mixture.
Drop the dough by teaspoonfuls into a greased baking sheet.
Press lightly with a fork to flatten. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 dozen cookies.

title: butterscotch banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine bananas, sugar, eggs and butter; beat until creamy.
Gradually add flour mixture alternately with milk; mix until well blended.
Stir in 2 cups chopped pecans and Nestle butterscotch morsels.

title: cheesey potato skins
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Scrub potatoes, pierce potato to allow steam to escape.
Bake about 45 minutes or until tender.
Let stand until cool enough to handle.
Cut potatoes lengthwise into fourths; carefully scoop out the pulp, leaving 1/4 inch potato in the shells.
Save the potato pulp for another use.
Set oven control to broil.
Place potato shells, skin side down, on a pan. Brush with butter.
Broil with tops 4 to 5 inches from the heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp and brown.
Sprinkle tomato and cheese over potato.
Broil about 30 seconds or until cheese is melted.
Top with sour cream; sprinkle with green onions.

title: diabetic orange salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Then chill until firm.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except popcorn in saucepan.
Cook until soft ball forms when a few drops of mixture are placed in a cup of cold water.
Pour over popcorn; mix thoroughly and form into balls.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, margarine, then eggs.
Add gradually dry ingredients, raisins and vanilla.
Bake on greased cookie sheet or greased Teflon at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put in blender and puree.

title: baked potato spears
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into thick slices.
Cut slices into strips.
Brush with salad dressing.
Place on greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until tender and golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: In a sealable bag, combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper. Toss the potatoes in flour mixture.
Melt butter in shallow baking dish.
Put potatoes in a single layer in dish.
Bake 1 hour in 375° oven, turning once after 30 minutes.

title: honey dijon dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a glass container.
Cap tightly and shake vigorously.
Chill until ready to use.
Flavor improves when chilled at least 24 hours.

title: chocolate nut drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter in a bowl.
Beat egg and then add the egg and milk.
Sift flour, baking powder and cocoa; add to mixture, then add nuts.
Stir well.
Drop with spoon on greased baking sheet and bake in hot oven (375°) for 15 minutes.

title: raisin cake
directions: Stew raisins in 2 cups water for 15 minutes; let cool.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Blend eggs, sugar and shortening. Blend to dry ingredients.
Add milk, raisins and dates.
Pour into three loaf pans 1/3 full.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Store in refrigerator.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan cook onion, celery and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Add tomatoes, water and seasonings. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer over low heat, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Add 3/4 cup Mozzarella cheese; stir until smooth.

title: foundation sweet dough
directions: Dissolve 2 packages yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water sweetened with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes, then stir well. Scald milk.
Add oleo, 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Add 2 cups flour to make a batter.
Add yeast mixture and 3 beaten eggs.
Beat well.
Add 5 cups flour, more or less, to make a soft dough.
Knead lightly and place in greased bowl.
Cover and set in warm place.
Let rise 2 hours or until double in bulk.
Punch down and use however you wish.
Good for rolls and kuchen.

title: buttermilk chocolate cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in bowl.
In saucepan bring to boil oleo, cocoa, water and oil.
Pour over flour mixture.
Beat and add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and soda.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Cook beef, garlic, onion and green pepper in heavy skillet over medium heat, stirring frequently to break up meat.
Cook until onion is soft and meat has lost its pink color.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat. Simmer the chili for 45 minutes, stirring frequently.
For hot chili, add Tabasco or cayenne pepper.
For thicker, add masa (corn flour).

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix condensed milk with lemon juice.
Add crushed pineapple and nuts.
Stir in whipped topping and pour into a 10-inch graham cracker crumb crust.
Sprinkle with coconut and chill.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar together; drain pineapple, then add the pineapple and pecans into Cool Whip, mixing.
Pour ingredients into pie crust.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cream and salt. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Put rhubarb on top. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer or until pie sets like custard. Cool before cutting.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch plate.
Spread cooked, drained broccoli in dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese graciously on top, evenly. Add chicken, shredded on top of Parmesan cheese.
Mix soup, sour cream, mayo, lemon juice, grated cheese and curry powder together in bowl.
Pour on top of chicken.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese again graciously on top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, onion and cheese in plate.
Beat together milk, eggs and Bisquick for 1 minute until smooth.
Pour into pie plate and bake 35 to 40 minutes until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes. Serve.

title: lemon spread
directions: Combine all, except butter, in small saucepan over low heat. Gradually bring to a boil (15 minutes).
Cool.
Beat in butter. Cover and chill.
Good on muffins and crackers.

title: eggnog fondue
directions: Pour eggnog into fondue pot.
Mix cornstarch with 1/2 ounce liquor; stir into eggnog.
Cook at medium, stirring, until mixture is thickened.
Add remaining liquor.
Keep warm at low for serving.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon.
Discard bones and dark skin. Fork into flakes. Mix salmon with crumbs, salt and pepper. Beat eggs slightly.
Add to mixture with mayonnaise and margarine.
Shape into patties and fry in oil until brown on both sides.

title: chinese dish (special)(this is a war time recipe.)
directions: Brown lean pork cubes slowly with salt, onion, garlic and fat. Add chicken bouillon cubes, dissolved in boiling water.
Cook slowly 10 minutes.
Add green pepper and celery.
Cover.
Cook 5 minutes.
Slowly blend in cornstarch, soy sauce and cold water; cook until thick, stirring constantly.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch baking pan, place frozen broccoli in pan with 2 tablespoon pats of butter.
Cut up chicken into bite size pieces and place on top of broccoli.

title: cinnamon cream cheese squares
directions: Unroll one tube of dough; place in lightly greased 9 x 13 pan.
Seal seams.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix dressing and sauerkraut.
Make sauce of butter, flour, cream and Dijon.
Place noodles in casserole, then corned beef, 1/2 cheese sauce, sauerkraut and rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: icing for chocolate cake
directions: Bring to a boil the butter, cocoa and milk.
Remove from heat and add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Use with Chocolate Cake from this same book.

title: mike's favorite tuna delight
directions: Boil and drain noodles according to package directions.
Mix tuna, soup and noodles together.
Cook in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and drizzle Hershey's syrup over top. Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts. Serve with cherry on top.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant and onions.
Slice in medium rounds.
Stem and seed pepper and cut into rings.
Cook in salted water until tender. Drain.
Place in casserole.
Season with garlic salt and pepper. Cover with cheese and bake in hot oven at 375° for 20 minutes. Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, vanilla and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well, stir in dry ingredients.
Fold in bananas.
Bake in 2 small loaf pans or 1 large pan, greased, for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: quick bishop's bread
directions: Combine Bisquick and sugar in a bowl and mix well.
Add orange juice and beaten eggs to the first mixture.
Stir in raisins, candied fruit and almonds.
Put in a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: wild rice with mushrooms and almonds
directions: Rinse and drain wild rice.
In large skillet, cook and stir almonds, onions and grains in butter until almonds are golden. Pour mixture into a greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole.
Heat broth to boiling, stir into grains.
Cover tightly and bake at 324 F for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until liquid is absorbed.
This recipe holds very well for several hours.

title: christmas crackers
directions: Make peanut butter sandwiches with crackers.
Dip in white chocolate and wax.
Cool.

title: artichoke dip
directions: In a baking dish, combine artichokes, mayonnaise and 2 cheeses. Sprinkle with garlic and pepper. Bake in oven for approximately 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Heat to bubble.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put Swiss cheese on each breast.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over chicken breasts.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pecan pie bars
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl mix 3 cups flour, sugar and margarine.
Mix until size of coarse meal.
Press into bottom of pan evenly.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix chocolate with butter in saucepan.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly, until blended.
Remove from heat; blend in evaporated milk gradually.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in a bowl.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Blend in chocolate mixture gradually.
Mix in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until puffed and brown.
Cover with aluminum foil if it browns too fast.
Cool completely so it will set.

title: ted's eggs
directions: Melt butter in cast-iron or nonstick medium size skillet. Break eggs into skillet, stirring constantly with spatula.
When eggs are set, but not dry, fold in cottage cheese.
Serve at once on preheated plates.

title: dorothea's wassail
directions: Combine the cider, juice and brown sugar in a 30-cup coffee maker.
Add cinnamon sticks.
Place remaining spices in basket with fruit which has been sliced.
Put lid on coffee maker and plug in. Allow to go through cycle, then serve.

title: easy cherry delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch glass pan, spread the crushed pineapple on bottom, then spread cherry pie filling over top of crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of cherry pie filling.
Slice margarine over top of dry cake mix. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
(You can use any pie filling.)

title: poppy seed fruit salad
directions: Mix apricots (juice and all) with pudding mix and poppy seed. Add drained pineapple, drained oranges, drained peaches and fresh fruit.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve in a dish with cubed bread to dip.
Great with Italian or pumpernickel bread.

title: kassidy's "another saturday night" steak marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in small saucepan.
Bring to boil over low heat.
Brush over steaks and marinate about 1 hour.
Brush remainder on steaks while grilling.
This sauce is also good for roasts.

title: fish alyeska
directions: Mix the mayonnaise, sour cream and onions together.
Put fillets in a shallow baking pan.
Spread mixture over uncooked fillets.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey or chicken rollettes florentine
directions: Flatten cutlets.
Combine spinach, bread crumbs, cheese and egg.
Spread mixture over cutlets.
Roll with stuffing inside and place seam side down in non stick baking dish.
Combine tomato sauce, wine, onion and garlic.
Pour over cutlets.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover during last 20 minutes of baking.
Spoon on sauce.
Serves 8.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender in a small amount of salted water (salt to taste).
Drain and combine with white sauce, American cheese and eggs.
Turn into a greased baking dish, sprinkle with the buttered crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until browned.

title: pumpkin bread(4th place at montgomery co. fair, maryland)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating very well.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with pumpkin and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla. Put in 2 greased, floured loaf pans.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix together and form into crust in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: apple-scotch cookies
directions: In small bowl, combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
In large bowl, combine brown sugar and butter; beat until fluffy. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chips, apples and oats.
Using a rounded tablespoon for each cookie, drop dough onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove to wire rack. Cool completely.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In 6-quart saucepan, in hot oil, brown roast on all sides. Spoon off fat.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup water.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 2 hours.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 45 minutes or until roast and vegetables are fork-tender.

title: honey dijon turkey (or chicken)
directions: In shallow baking dish, combine honey Dijon dressing, water, garlic, ginger, red pepper and turkey.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator, stirring occasionally, at least 2 hours.
In large skillet, bring turkey with marinade to a boil.
Reduce heat and continue cooking, stirring occasionally, 3 minutes or until turkey is almost done.
Stir in green onions and cook an additional minute or until the turkey is done.
Serve over hot rice.

title: blueberry banana bread
directions: Mix together flours, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in oats.
Add oil, eggs, bananas and blueberries.
Stir just until mixed.

title: rice casserole
directions: In a skillet, place the first 6 ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes or until the rice is golden.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put into casserole and bake until rice absorbs the liquid (20 to 30 minutes).
Stir while baking, once.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: cream caramel
directions: Butter a square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Spread nuts into pan. Heat sugar, corn syrup, margarine and 1 cup half and half to boiling in saucepan on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in remaining half and half.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently to 245°.
Immediately spread over nuts in pan; cut into squares.

title: poor man's stroganoff
directions: Sprinkle paprika and garlic powder on meat to coat lightly. Mix undiluted soups together and pour over meat.
Bake in 275° oven for 4 hours.
Check occasionally to stir and add water, if needed.
During the last 1/2 hour, add 1/2 pint sour cream.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spread hash browns in bottom of rectangular casserole dish. Mix cheese, onion, soup, sour cream and 1 stick butter and spread over hash browns. Coat crushed cornflakes with other stick of melted butter and spread over casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: marshmallow treats
directions: Melt in microwave.
Stick toothpicks in jumbo marshmallows. Dip marshmallow in caramel sauce.
Roll in Rice Krispies.

title: sussex county slick dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt and shortening with fingers until all lumps disappear.
Add hot water gradually to make a soft dough.
Roll out to desired thickness and cut into 4 inch squares.
Cook approximately 15 minutes in boiling broth.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and syrup together in heavy saucepan and bring to soft ball stage. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and peanut butter and beat until thick and creamy. Pour into pan to cool.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and margarine.
Spread in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of pretzel layer.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add strawberries. Refrigerate until mixture is partially thickened.
Spread on top of cheese layer and chill thoroughly before serving.

title: no cook lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add sauce and water.
Blend well and simmer 5 minutes.
In a bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, chives, oregano and egg; mix well.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put 1 1/2 cup meat sauce.
Add 1/2 of the noodles, 1/2 of the cheese mixture and 1/2 of the Mozzarella.
Repeat.
On top put remaining meat sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until bubbly.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove skin and bone.
Cook rice as package says.
Stir all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and
bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Makes 3 large layers.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat; spoon off excess fat; add next 6 ingredients. Simmer until thick, 45 minutes to one hour, stirring occasionally. Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain; rinse in cold water.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs slightly with beater; beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Reduce heat; bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: whipped frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk in small saucepan.
Cook over medium-low heat until thick.
Set off heat and cool until cold.
Cream sugar, margarine and vanilla until fluffy.
Mix cold flour mixture into sugar mixture and whip well for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes enough for a sheet cake.
Double recipe for layer cake.

title: american beauty cake
directions: Mix food coloring and Nestle Quik; let stand.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and food coloring mixture.
Beat very well.
Add remaining ingredients except vinegar and baking soda.
Beat at medium speed 2 to 3 minutes.
Dissolve soda in vinegar and add to mixture and mix by hand.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: noodle kugel(jewish noodle pudding)
directions: Mix well.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with topping.

title: chewies
directions: Mix all together and spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mixture will be sticky.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut in squares while hot and remove from pan.

title: diet strawberry cheese cake
directions: Empty D-Zerta mix in small mixing bowl.
Add 1 cup water.
Mix until fluffy.
Put in small pieces of cream cheese.
Mix well. Add strawberries; put Equal over strawberries and let dissolve. Put in refrigerator until it gets cold.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Scald milk. Add salt, oil and sugar. Pour over yeast. Add flour. Knead a few times. Roll out and cut rolls. Brush with butter. Let rise 1 hour. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill 6 hours.
Serve with tray of assorted raw vegetables such as carrots, celery strips, sliced cucumbers, green peppers, cherry tomatoes or cauliflower.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: In large cooler combine all ingredients, stirring Kool-Aid, sugar and water well first.
Add lots of ice.
Pour in ginger ale just before serving.
Makes at least 75 servings.

title: veggie-pasta salad
directions: Mix together the onions, celery, broccoli, mushrooms, tomatoes, pepper, olives and garlic.
Add the olive oil and seasonings to mixture and toss; set aside.

title: peanut butter, yam and pumpkin soup(a rich velvety smooth, flavorful soup)
directions: Melt butter in a soup pot over medium heat. Stir in pie filling, sweet potatoes and peanut butter. Add broth, pepper and salt; stir well until smooth. Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes. To serve, garnish soup with chives and sour cream. Serves 8.

title: homemade vegetable beef soup
directions: Put ingredients all together in cook pot.
Let cook all day. Start in morning; should be done by dinner.

title: crumbly top apple pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Arrange apple slices in unbaked pie shell.
Blend brown sugar and flour.
Cut in butter or margarine with pastry blender until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake in moderately hot oven at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with or without cream.

title: irene's tomato aspic ring
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; mix tomato juice, bay leaves, salt, celery, onions and cayenne.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Strain. Dissolve gelatin thoroughly in hot tomato mixture.
Add vinegar and lemon juice; turn into a 1 1/2-quart ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: caramel dip
directions: Use for dipping apple slices or any fresh fruit that is in season.

title: deer bologna
directions: Mix well.
Make into oblong rolls.
Wrap in Saran Wrap or waxed paper.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Remove paper.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 225° for 3 hours.

title: trout amandine
directions: Dip trout in milk.
Season with salt and pepper and roll in flour.
Cook the trout in butter until evenly browned on both sides.
Remove fish and saute the chopped almonds in the butter. Sprinkle generously over the fish.
Serves 6.

title: tasty meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Grease loaf pan and pack.
Bake 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hash brown au gratin potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients for casserole together and pour in a greased 9 x 13 inch casserole dish.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Mix well and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done; cool.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken, cool and shred.
Boil broccoli. Grease an 11 x 7-inch casserole dish.
Place chicken on bottom, then broccoli. Combine mayonnaise, soup, curry powder and lemon juice.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with mixture of cheese and bread crumbs. Top with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: low cholesterol squash casserole
directions: Cook squash with finely chopped onions, then drain.
Melt margarine in hot milk; add crumbs, squash, salt and pepper.
Add Egg Beaters.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole (use Pam).
If desired, top with extra buttered crumbs or low-fat cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Put rhubarb in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan. Top with sugar and red jello.
Sprinkle miniature marshmallows over that.
Top with yellow cake mix, mixed according to directions.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Will be shaky when done.
Turn out on plate.

title: corn sticks
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put generously greased corn stick pans in 475° oven and preheat for 5 minutes.
Remove and add corn bread mixture.
Pans will sizzle.
Bake at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Fills two pans.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour slowly.
Dough will be soft and smooth.
Chill dough.
This cookie can be rolled between wax paper and cut 1/4 inch thick (small cutter).
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes or until very light brown.

title: english apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture in small pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: italian eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant into 1/2-inch slices and sprinkle with salt, let stand 20 minutes.
Pat dry.
Dip each slice in the flour, salt and pepper.
Fry in hot oil.
Lay on paper towel.
Pour 1/4 of sauce in a 2-quart casserole and layer with 1/3 eggplant slices.
Repeat eggplant, sauce and cheeses.
Cover and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 more minutes.

title: spinach dip(appetizers)
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package.
Drain well. Mix all ingredients.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: quick pizza dip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread cream cheese on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, pizza sauce and remaining Mozzarella cheese.

title: pecan pralines
directions: In a large pan, combine sugar, soda and salt.
Stir in buttermilk and Karo.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir to hard ball.
Remove from heat; add oleo.
Stir in pecans.
Beat until mixture is thick enough to drop, perhaps 5 to 6 minutes.
Drop on wax paper.
If mixture gets too stiff, add 1 teaspoon of hot water.

title: irish bread
directions: Sift together the already sifted flour with the sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add the raisins and caraway seed to the dry mixture.
Mix together the eggs, buttermilk and Crisco. Combine with dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
(I bake it in a greased cast-iron skillet.)

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into small balls; chill at least 1 hour.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls in mixture.
Cool on wax paper.
Lots of calories?
Who cares.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in glass baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: broiler cake
directions: Put 2 tablespoons butter in milk.
Heat.
Mix altogether the sugar, eggs, flour, vanilla and baking powder.
Add heated milk and butter gradually.
This will make a thin batter.
Bake about 30 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
When baked and still hot, frost with brown sugar, cream, 2 tablespoons melted butter and coconut mixture.
Return cake to the oven and broil until frosting has caramelized.
Cool.
Enjoy.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients with mixer.
Cream remaining ingredients by hand.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan for 30 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together first six ingredients.
Mix together corn flakes and margarine and spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Saute onion in butter. Add ground beef and brown.
Drain well. Combine meat mixture with remaining ingredients in a crock-pot. Heat until cheeses melt.
Serve with corn chips.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; set aside.
Combine buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and alternate with milk mixture to creamed ingredients.
Drop from a tablespoon onto slightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 13 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Cake: Place cake in trifle bowl or other large glass bowl. Pour orange juice over cake cubes; set aside. In blender, puree 1 pint strawberries with 4 tablespoons sugar; pour over cake. Slice remaining strawberries; arrange over cake. Set aside.

title: cinderella crisps
directions: Using two forks, roll bread in condensed milk, coating both sides, then roll in coconut.
Place on well-greased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove at once from sheet. Makes 24.

title: hamburger oriental
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add celery and onion; saute until onion is transparent.
Combine with soups, milk and soy sauce.
Place in Pam-sprayed ovenproof dish.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake for 30 minutes (can substitute cream of mushroom soup).

title: english pancakes
directions: Mix all together, until smooth. Make as you would American pancakes, except British pancakes a large ( about 8 inches across) and thin. Toss and turn. Sprinkle with sugar and lemon. Roll up.

title: italian sausage balls
directions: Put everything in bowl and mix.
Make balls.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
After baked, put toothpicks in balls.
They are great for a party.

title: hard candy
directions: Sprinkle with powdered sugar a strip (18 x 24-inch) aluminum foil (heavy).
Mix sugar, corn syrup and water in large, heavy saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Boil, without stirring, until temperature reaches 310°.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flavoring and food coloring and pour on foil.

title: danish puff
directions: Measure 1 level cup flour into bowl.
Using hands, blend in 1 stick of the margarine.
When combined, sprinkle with 2 to 3 tablespoons cold water.
Round into ball with hands; divide in half.
Pat each half onto baking sheet with non-stick surface, creating 2 oblongs, each about 12 x 4 1/2 x 1/8-inch.
The oblongs should be about 1-inch apart.

title: asparagus salad with mustardy dressing
directions: Snap or cut off tough ends of asparagus spears.
If desired, peel stalks.
Bring 1-inch of water to a boil in a frying pan. Add asparagus in an even layer.
Cook until spears are a bright green and are tender-crisp when pierced, 4 minutes (1 or 2 minutes if peeled).
Lift out asparagus; drain briefly.
Arrange spears on a serving plate.
Cover and chill at least 30 minutes.

title: radish and cream cheese spread
directions: Mix cheese, butter, celery salt, paprika and Worcestershire sauce together until smooth.
Stir in radishes and onions.
Chill several hours to blend flavors.
Spread on crackers.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: tuna bake
directions: Blend cheese into soup with mixer.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix crumbs with butter and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Dissolve jell-o in hot water and let cool.
Mix all ingredients and bake for 30 minutes at 350° Bundt pan.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients, except salt in 10 to 12-quart stainless steel pot.
Bring to boil, stir, cover, and simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Add salt to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lazy lemon pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk.
Have lemonade thawed and pour into milk and Cool Whip.
Stir good and pour into graham cracker crust. Chill and serve.

title: tea rings(basic sweet dough)
directions: Combine milk, sugar, salt and butter in a small pan; heat over low heat.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: wheat rolls
directions: Stir together white flour and yeast.
Heat milk, water, oil, sugar and salt until very warm (120° to 130°; use candy thermometer).
Add liquid all at once to flour-yeast mixture. Beat at medium speed of mixer until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Add enough flour to form soft dough.
Mix well (either by hand or use mixer).
Let stand 12 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix, simmer and pour over ribs.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Boil all ingredients until al dente.

title: easy squash casserole
directions: Mix mashed squash, pineapple and brown sugar.
Place in casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Warm cottage cheese.
Dissolve soda in cheese liquid. Add beaten egg, soda, sugar, oleo, salt and yeast mixture.
Stir in flour, dill seed and onion flakes.
Cover. Let rise 1 hour.
Stir down.
Pat in a 9-inch casserole. Cover and let rise until double (about 40 minutes). Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Brush top with oleo. Sprinkle with coarse salt.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Bake chicken in oven for 30 minutes; cut in cubes when cool. Fry some wontons which have been cut in 3 or 4 pieces in small amount of oil until lightly browned, then cut in small pieces and add to salad just before serving.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts well; chop finely.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake approximately 15 minutes at 350°, then broil until brown.
Serve with Triscuits crackers.

title: foster's favorite fast food
directions: Pour eggs beaten with milk into buttered medium-hot skillet. Sprinkle on meat and cheese.
Fold over when cheese is melted and eggs are almost done.
Slide onto plate when done.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into patties. Cook in oil until golden brown.

title: alabama hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown meat with onion and green pepper.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Heat through and pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Add sharp Cheddar cheese to taste.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese with cucumber and tomato.
Mix well and serve.

title: green rice
directions: Saute celery and onions until limp but not brown.
Combine cooked rice, broccoli, onions and celery.
Add chicken soup, mushrooms and Cheez Whiz.
Mix well and pour in casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pork and sauerkraut dinner(easy dinner for a busy day)
directions: Turn slow cooker to high.
Mix envelope of soup mix with 3/4 cup of hot tap water.
Pour this strong soup mix in the crock. Trim roast of external fat and cut it into large chunks.
Place in crock.
Rinse and drain sauerkraut twice.
Add to the crock.
Mix the brown sugar into the applesauce and pour over the pork and sauerkraut.
Cover and cook on high for about 5 hours or until the pork is fall-apart tender.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Sprinkle top with minced onions. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
In large skillet, heat corn oil over medium heat.
Add next 3 ingredients; stir-fry 2 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Remove and stir-fry chicken approximately 3 minutes.
In bowl, stir together pineapple juice and remaining 5 ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Add green pepper mixture and pineapple.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat. Cook for 1 minute.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 2 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup wheat flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids until very warm, 120° to 130°. Add dry ingredients.
Beat well. Stir in remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Shape to fit into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans that have been sprinkled with cornmeal or wheat germ.
Cover. Let rise in warm place for 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately and cool. Yields 2 loaves.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In saucepan heat beans, soup, chili powder, and garlic salt; set aside.
Saute meat, onions, and salt; set aside.
Place 1/2 of tortillas in bottom of greased casserole dish; layer meat mixture, bean mixture, and sliced cheese.
Place remaining tortillas on top.
Top with tomatoes and monterey jack cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving.

title: trang's grilled chicken
directions: Brown garlic, sesame seed and onion in oil.
Let cool.
Add salt and pepper, sugar and sauces.
Soak chicken overnight.
When you put chicken in sauce, put in one piece at a time.
When all pieces have been coated, pour remaining sauce over chicken.
Great for grilling!
You can double recipe for larger amount of marinade.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup with beef, rice, onion and salt.
Shape firmly into 16 meatballs.
Brown meatballs and garlic in shortening; pour off fat.
Blend in remaining soup, water and mustard.
Cover.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until done.
Stir now and then.

title: lemon lush
directions: Blend margarine and flour. Press crust into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

Blend cream cheese and confectioners sugar. Add 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust. Sprinkle with nuts. Blend pudding with 3 cups milk. Spread over previous layer. Refrigerate for 1/2 hour. Top with remaining Cool Whip and nuts.

title: hummus (chickpea spread)
directions: Put chick peas, garlic and salt in food processor with 1/2 cup water and tahini.
Add lemon juice and rest of water slowly until it is the consistency of a smooth paste, suitable for dipping. Good with pita bread triangles.

title: hot fudge cream puffs
directions: In a medium saucepan, crumble pie crust into boiling water; cook and stir vigorously until pastry forms a ball and leaves side of pan.
Remove from heat; cool for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating with a wooden spoon after each addition until smooth.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in a greased and floured sheet cake pan for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: date nut roll
directions: Mix sugar, milk and dates in boiler. Cook, stirring constantly until it forms a firm ball in cold water. Take off heat and beat until it begins to thicken. Add nuts, butter and vanilla. Wring a cotton dish towel out in cold water and spread on table. When candy is as thick as can be stirred, pour lengthwise in middle of dish towel, roll it over and let stand in refrigerator until candy is cold. Unwrap and slice.

title: shipwreck
directions: Layer potatoes, ground beef and onion in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour kidney beans on mixture. Spread the undiluted tomato soup over beans and sprinkle with chili powder to taste.
Cover with foil. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat pudding, sugar and milk until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip. Lightly butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place layer of crackers. Spread 1/2 of the pudding mixture.
Place another layer of crackers.
Spread with rest of pudding mixture.
Place another layer of crackers.
Cover with chocolate frosting; cover with chopped nuts.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chicken olivia
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Put in casserole dish sprayed with vegetable spray.
Mix last 3 ingredients.
Spread over top and cook at 325° in oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over butter; spread out.
Cook at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Add vanilla, mix well.
Add flour alternately with chocolate.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.

title: pita chips
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Split each pita bread into 2 round pieces (whole wheat pita bread has more fiber).
Cut each half into 6 triangles with kitchen scissors.
Arrange in a single layer on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle lightly with garlic powder, if desired. Bake for 8 minutes until chips are lightly browned and very crisp.
Store in an airtight container.

title: raisin pie
directions: Place raisins and water in saucepan.
Cook for 20 minutes. Measure 2 cups of the juice of the raisins and water; add tapioca and sugar.
Cook for 8 minutes until it begins to thicken. Gradually add egg yolks to the mixture.
Continue cooking until thick.
Stir in butter and lemon juice.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: vanilla pudding with bulacha maria(portuguese)
directions: Make pudding by following package directions.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding.
Dip Bulacha Maria in coffee one by one and layer on the bottom of serving dish.
Pour pudding and garnish.
Preparation time:
20 minutes.

title: peach muffins
directions: Place sugar, vegetable oil, eggs, pumpkin and water in bowl and mix.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Stir into first mixture.
Add raisins and walnuts.
Let stand 1 hour at room temperature.
Place in greased muffin pans.
Bake in preheated 400° oven approximately 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook squash and onion together until tender and drain. In large bowl, combine stuffing, cheese (cut up), eggs and mushroom soup. Put squash in bowl. Mix. Put mixture in casserole dish. Cover with crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Bake 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in food chopper.
Pour sugar over berries and let set 2 hours.
Mix jello and hot water and set aside.
After 2 hours, mix celery, nuts, apples and cranberries and add to jello mixture.
Place in refrigerator and chill.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Brown stew meat.
Add diced potatoes and mushroom soup.
Cook on low temperature all day.
Last hour add mushrooms and sour cream.
Last 15 minutes, add sharp shredded cheese.

title: nutty oat waffles
directions: Blend ingredients smooth.
(For best results, refrigerate overnight.) Bake in hot waffle iron, sprayed or oiled, for 8 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 (6-inch) waffles.
Freezes well.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cook cake in 2 layers.
Mix all other ingredients together and spread.
You can use 2 layers or pound cake.

title: laura bush's cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in bowl.

title: ida's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add dry mixture and milk alternately to sugar mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Fold in flavorings.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: toasted almond spread
