directions: Mix all ingredients (reserve some of the almonds) and spread in a 9-inch pie pan or quiche dish.
Sprinkle reserved almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until brown and bubbly. Serve with crackers.

title: picnic baked beans
directions: Dice the bacon and onion.
Saute in small skillet until bacon is thoroughly cooked.
Put beans, mustard, catsup and brown sugar in 2-quart casserole and mix well.
Drain bacon-onion mixture and add to casserole.
Mix again and bake 50 minutes at 375°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix spices and sugar and pour over apples.
Let stand 1 hour. Add eggs, oil and vanilla and blend.
Add flour, salt and soda (sifted together), stirring until just blended.
Add raisins and nuts and mix.
Pour into greased, wax paper-lined 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Freezes well.

title: peanut krisp bars
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup until dissolved, blend in peanut butter.
Stir in cereal.
Pack evenly in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch cake pan.
Melt margarine and brown sugar, add milk and vanilla.
Add confectioners sugar.
Beat until smooth and spread on top of peanut butter mixture.
Cool.

title: microwave chocolate sauce
directions: Microwave unsweetened and sweet chocolate with butter 2 minutes until bubbly.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla and evaporated milk; microwave 8 more minutes on Medium-high.

title: oriental-style franks
directions: Mix water, soy sauce, honey, sugar, cornstarch, garlic powder and ginger.
Cook frankfurters or sausage in oil, just until edges begin to curl.
Stir in soy sauce mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and frankfurters or sausages are evenly coated.
Stir in green onion.
Serve with fancy wooden picks.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together in a large saucepan.
Turn off heat; add sugar and eggs.
Mix together; add cornstarch and mix. Add vanilla and milk.
Stir together.
Cook over medium heat, stirring with a spatula because it sticks and burns easily once it starts thickening.
Stir constantly.
When thickened, pour in pie shell.
Add nuts before pouring, if desired.
Garnish with Cool Whip before serving.
Very rich.

title: chicken-cheese enchiladas
directions: In a small bowl, combine soup and milk; set the bowl aside.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add and beat well the oil, grated zucchini, vanilla and sugar.
Add and mix well the remaining ingredients. Pour into greased and floured loaf pans (makes 2 loaves).
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes (test for doneness).

title: trifle
directions: Put jelly rolls in bowl (medium to large size).
They may be cut up, if you wish.
Drain fruit cocktail and put on top of jelly rolls.
Pour sherry in and set aside.

title: beef barbecue
directions: In a large pan, saute onions in butter over medium heat.
Add vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, prepared mustard, brown sugar, catsup and water.
Bring to a slow boil.
Add diced beef.
Simmer until liquid is thickened to desired consistency.
Stir occasionally to keep it from sticking.

title: quick potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in skins.
Peel and slice into 1/4 to 1/2-inch slices.
Place in casserole.
Measure enough milk to cover potatoes.
Put salt, pepper and garlic salt into the milk.
Stir in enough cracker crumbs to thicken mixture.
Pour in margarine, stir in cheese.
Pour this mixture over potatoes, top with cracker crumbs.
Place in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peach-honey sorbet
directions: Puree peaches in their juice along with honey and lemon juice. Freeze.
Remove sorbet just before it gets too solid and puree again.
Put back into freezer until ready to serve.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Wash chicken and place in a large pot with enough water to cover well.
Add salt, pepper, carrot and celery.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and cook at a gentle boil for about 45 minutes to an hour.
Be sure to add more water if it gets low.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer with half of cooked broccoli, macaroni and cheese, grated cheese, lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Repeat.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°, then add toasted bread crumbs and cook 15 minutes more.

title: red fish courtbouillon
directions: Clean, cut up and boil fish with salt and pepper until tender. Drain in colander; save broth.
Make roux with oil and flour. Add onions, celery and bell peppers and cook until onions are translucent.
Add tomato paste and a pinch of soda.
Cook slowly until fat separates.
Add whole tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add enough of the fish broth to get the right fish taste.
Cook about 3 to 4 hours slowly.
Season to taste.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Mix well tomato soup and cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients and season to taste.
Pour into mold and chill thoroughly.
Serves 8 guests.

title: grape delight salad
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and lemon juice in top of double boiler. Cook over hot water until thickened.
Remove from heat and cool. Fold in whipping cream.
Then add well-drained fruit and remaining ingredients.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.
Very light and delicious.

title: five soup hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together; drain off fat.
Add soups and mix well.
Fold in 2/3 of noodles.
Place in a large casserole, 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield: 10 servings.
Carbohydrate 25 g, protein 23 g, fat 23 g, calories 399.
One serving = 3 medium fat exchange, 1 1/2 bread starch exchange, 2 fat exchange.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in one bowl, then add remaining ingredients.
Use paper cupcake holders or just cupcake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use toothpick for doneness. Makes 30 to 36 per batch.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat, add onions and garlic.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add next 9 ingredients; simmer 2 hours.
Use thin layer of sauce first so noodles will not stick to pan.
Layer cooked noodles, 1 layer Parmesan cheese, 1 layer cottage or Ricotta cheese, 1 layer Mozzarella cheese and 1 layer sauce.

title: pumpkin rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Grease cookie sheet and cover with wax paper. Spread mix on wax paper. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. While in oven, take a paper towel (2 pieces) and sprinkle it with powdered sugar. Take cake out of oven and lay on towel. Take wax paper off and roll up, using the length of the towel. Let cool.

title: beef stew
directions: Heat over medium heat or in casserole in oven.
Serve plain or over hot biscuits, toast or noodles.

title: great-grandma's top of the stove cookies
directions: Boil together one minute the milk, butter, cocoa, sugar and salt.
Next add peanut butter and vanilla.
Then remove from heat and stir in oats.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: martha washington centers
directions: Beat ingredients.
Use as soft cream center for bonbon mold. Can add flavors, if desired.
Can be frozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into a baked 9-inch pie shell.
Chill and serve.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well. Squeeze to remove moisture.
Combine rest of ingredients with spinach.
Shape into balls.
Can be baked now or frozen.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: cheese pastry
directions: Make your favorite pastry.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend peanut butter, margarine and sugar.
Add 1/2 cup flour, soda and baking powder.
In
saucepan, bring to boil the milk, vanilla and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Mix in 2 1/4 cups flour until well blended.
Shape into balls and flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix.
Make into 2 rolls and chill for an hour.
Slice and bake.

title: kildee's chicken salad
directions: Cook peas according to package directions.
Combine all other ingredients.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the dry mixture.
Add the rest of the ingredients into the well. Stir, do not beat.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan or Bundt cake pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting (the same kind you would use on a Carrot Cake).

title: clyde's salad dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients first, then add other ingredients.
Mix or shake well.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 quarts.
Delicious!

title: rice casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cover with foil and cook in 350° oven for 1 hour or cover with wax paper and cook on High for 20 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Slowly mix sugar into beaten eggs.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 1 hour at 325° in metal pan or at 300° in glass.

title: rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine rice and onions.
Blend cottage cheese, garlic (chopped), sour cream, milk, Tabasco sauce and salt.
Stir into rice mixture and turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 25 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crackers and cheese.
Pour mixture into baking dish.
Top with crushed crackers and cheese. Bake at 350° until firm and lightly browned, 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan and simmer on stove until vegetables are tender.

title: brenda s.'s coca-cola cake
directions: Bring Coke, cocoa and margarine to a boil.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into boiled mixture and blend until smooth.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blend all together.
Put into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add broccoli until tender.
Add rest of ingredients and stir.
Bake in buttered dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lazy woman's cake
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl, except 1 cup water.
Mix well, then stir in the rest of the water.
Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 to 60 minutes.
Very moist cake!

title: mound cake
directions: Bring to a boil sugar and milk for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows.
Stir and let melt.
Add vanilla.
Bake 2 layers of devil's food cake.
Split each to make 4 layers.
Spread filling between and on top.
Refrigerate.
Better the 2nd or 3rd day.

title: frosted banana bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, sour cream and vanilla. Combine flour, baking soda and salt; gradually add to the creamed mixture. Stir in bananas. Spread into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour in pan on top of melted oleo.
Pour the can of fruit over top; don't stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red, white and blue
directions: First Layer:
Dissolve blackberry Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water in another bowl.
Add blueberry pie filling; mix well.
Pour slowly into a clear glass bowl.
Wipe splatters off glass.
Chill until set.

title: twice baked potato skins
directions: Slice potatoes lengthwise, season with Seasoning salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Heat a pot with vegetable oil, fry potatoes until soft in the middle.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees, spread cheeses and bacon bits on each slice of potato.
Cook until cheeses are melted.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute onions, peppers and meat. Add taco sauce and soup. Cook 15 minutes. Layer in pan, Doritos then meat. Put the cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in lard with pastry blender.
Put egg and vinegar in a 1 cup measure and stir up with fork.
Add cold water to egg and vinegar until it equals 1 cup.
Pour liquid in the bowl with flour mixture.
Stir with fork until well blended.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix milk and sour cream, then add Tang.
Pour in pie crust. Top with Cool Whip and pecans.
Chill overnight.

title: cranberry punch
directions: In a large pot or pitcher, dissolve the sugar in the hot water.
Add the cranberry, lemon and orange juices and stir. Chill.
Just before serving, add the sparkling water or ginger ale and pour over ice in the punch bowl.
Serves 3 quarts.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes for 30 minutes, peel, cut up and place in salad bowl.
Add celery and onion.
Mix together mayo, sugar, vinegar, relish and salt; gently toss potatoes to coat.
Slice eggs over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients in order given in large bowl with top.
Place in refrigerator until ready to bake.
Roll out on floured board and cut as large or small biscuits or put in muffin tin (well-greased).
Bake at 425° until browned.
Yields 50 biscuits. Preparation Time:
Until browned.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt the chocolate chips in a small pan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add the peanut butter.
Mix until smooth, then remove from heat.
Pour mixture over the cereal in a large bowl, mixing quickly to coat.
Transfer the mixture into a large, plastic bag or container with a cover.
Add the powdered sugar; shake.
Pour the mixture onto a cookie sheet to cool.
Store in a sealed container.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix well and finish filling the churn with whole milk.
Freeze according to churn directions.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: brownies
directions: Microwave chocolate and butter for 2 minutes. Stir until chocolate is melted. Stir in sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour and nuts. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.

title: easy pumpkin pie
directions: Stir eggs, salt, sugar, Bisquick and butter.
Add spice and milk; mix well.
Do not use pie crust!
Pour mixture into a greased 9-inch pie plate; bake for 40 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in large shallow casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over chicken; cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon, then saute onions in 2 tablespoons bacon fat. Simmer potatoes in water until tender.
Add bacon, onion, salt and pepper to cooked potatoes.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add milk and bring to boil.
Add clams and barely heat.
Serve with a dollop of butter and a pinch of thyme.
Top with parsley.

title: b~b~q brisket
directions: Sprinkle brisket generously with garlic salt.
Place in cooking bag.
Pour liquid smoke over brisket.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 275° for 6 hours or until tender.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts in top of double boiler. Place over simmering water and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix.
Spread candy quickly in buttered 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Yields 2 dozen pieces.

title: macaroni pie
directions: In large casserole dish place layer of macaroni and then layer of grated cheese, ending with cheese on top (should be at least 2 layers of each).
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over cheese and macaroni.
This mixture will come to the top of the cheese.
Place slices of butter on
top.
Bake at 425° until brown and done.

title: candy nuts
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream and corn syrup in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Continue to cook over low heat to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Cool to lukewarm, heating until mixture loses gloss. Add nuts quickly. Stir until coated.
Spread on foil.
Break apart when cool.
May be frozen.

title: m&m's cake
directions: Prepare the box of pudding according to package directions; set aside to cool.
Place slightly cooled pudding into a large mixing bowl.
Add dry cake mix to the pudding; omit eggs, oil and water.
Mix well and add chopped nuts (optional).
The batter will resemble thick brownie batter.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the bag of M&M's evenly over the top of the batter. Place into a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat milk, eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt together.
Put batter into greased square pan. Cut bread slices into cubes and place on top of batter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: preserving news articles(takes acid out)
directions: Mix and let set for 24 hours.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan, then put article in mixture for 2 hours.
Put on paper towel after taking it out of mixture.

title: barbecue spoonburgers
directions: Brown beef in hot oil in skillet. Discard excess fat.
Put remaining ingredients in slow cooker.
Add meat and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or on high 3 to 4 hours.
Spoon into warm hamburger buns or serve over rice, mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: candy bar cake
directions: Combine candy bars and 1/2 cup butter in a heavy saucepan; place over medium heat and stir constantly until candy bars melt.* Set aside.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder together 3 times. Cream Crisco well; add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add eggs, beating in well.
Add milk and flour, alternately, beating well. Add flavoring.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: hot sausage rolls
directions: Deviled eggs are an appetizer everyone enjoys.
This piquant version, flavored with ham, mustard and capers, is also good for a lunch salad.
Or add sliced cold meats and your favorite breads for a buffet supper.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix all together and pour in greased 13 X 9 pan. Cover and bake at 375 degrees for 2 hours.

title: lee's turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except for cornflakes) and pour into oblong pyrex pan or casserole dish. Cornflakes are then spread on top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes & serve hot.

title: fruit dreams
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, sugar, extract and lemon juice, mixing well until well blended.
Fold into whipped cream.
Spoon mixture onto waxed paper-covered cookie sheet to form 8 shells; freeze.
Fill center of each shell with fruit before serving. Yields 8 shells.

title: chocolate malt cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Mix.
Add flour and cocoa.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: hallie's peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir together flour, soda and salt.
In a mixer bowl beat butter for 30 seconds.
Add peanut butter and sugars.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture; beat until well combined.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar if desired. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet; crisscross with the tines of a fork.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.
Cool about 1 minute before removing to a wire rack.
Makes a whole bunch.
(Let the first pan burn because Hallie always did.)

title: po-man's ribs and rice
directions: Brown short ribs in oven.
Combine remaining ingredients, except rice, plus 1/2 cup water.
Pour over ribs.
Cover; simmer for about 2 1/2 hours.
Serve with hot, cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate drop candies
directions: Mix it all up together.
Make into little balls.
Put in refrigerator until dip is done.

title: doshie's pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs and beat until smooth. Add other ingredients.
Cook 10 minutes at 450°, then 50 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon italian cookies
directions: Sift flour.
Add baking powder and sugar and sift again.
Cut in shortening and add milk, egg and lemon extract.
Blend thoroughly.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Mix and pour over crust, cream cheese and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until firm.
Boil 2 cups water; add 2 small raspberry Jell-O and 1 package raspberries. Pour over top and refrigerate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
When ready to serve, combine apples, pineapple, marshmallows and whipped cream.
Toss together lightly and serve.

title: tea doughnuts
directions: Mix well.
Drop batter into deep fat at 365°.
Brown on both sides.
Drain and dust with powdered sugar.

title: chicken soup
directions: Place washed chicken in kettle with remaining ingredients. Bring just to boil.
Lower heat and simmer 2 hours or until chicken falls away from bone.
Remove chicken from broth; set aside.
Strain broth and return to pot.
If desired, the broth may be cooled and fat removed from the top.
Cooked noodles may be added at this point and the boned chicken returned to broth along with 1/4 cup parsley and 1 or 2 chicken bouillon cubes.
If chilled and skimmed of fat, proceed as directed with noodles, parsley and bouillon upon reheating.

title: strawberries and cream ice cream
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into freezer container of a 5-quart ice cream freezer.
Freeze to manufacturer's instructions.
Pack freezer and let sit 1 hour before serving.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pan except orange wedges. Slowly bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve in warm mugs with a clove studded orange wedge.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage and onion in just enough water to cook thoroughly.
Season to taste; drain.
Brown chuck and season; drain fat.
Mix all ingredients with cheese.
Sprinkle on top. Place in covered casserole dish and bake at 450° for 1 hour.

title: chicken devine
directions: Put raw rice in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add all soups to pan. Top with cut up chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 2 hours.

title: hawaiian carrots
directions: Drain juice from 1 can of the pineapple and add to sugar, butter and salt.
Boil 5 minutes.
In a baking dish alternate layers of carrot slices with layers of crushed pineapple.
Pour boiling syrup over all and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: filet with brandy, cream and green peppercorn
directions: In a bowl mix last 6 ingredients.
Set aside.

title: granny steele's banana-nut bread
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Place in loaf pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Recipe may be doubled and 1 loaf frozen.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In a boiler Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and butter.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Add oats and peanut butter and stir until thick.
Drop on wax paper by the teaspoonfuls.

title: henry's stuffed peppers
directions: Cut tops of peppers off; remove seeds from peppers.
Wash and drain.
Chop up the tops of the peppers to put with the other ingredients.
Mix all the ingredients with 1/2 cup of the tomato sauce.
Put this in peppers.
Place in pan.
Pour rest of the tomato sauce with equal amount of water over peppers.
Cook on medium heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: sad sack cookies
directions: Mix and bake on greased sheet pan at 325° until light brown.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix the 2 ingredients (dry) in large mixing bowl.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: Take one slice of dried beef and lay flat on surface.
Place one of the quarters of the dill pickle in the center.
Then, with a knife, cut a small portion of the cream cheese and place this also in the center with the pickle.
Roll up.
Place in airtight container or serve.

title: grouper with white wine
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Wash and dry grouper; place in an earthenware baking dish with 2 tablespoons melted butter, mushrooms and onions. Add the bay leaf, thyme, salt and pepper. Sprinkle with the bread crumbs and dot with the remaining butter. Pour the wine over all. Bake 20 to 45 minutes, depending on thickness, basting occasionally, until fish flakes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine meal, salt and soda and mix well.
Stir in shortening and eggs and mix well.
Stir in corn and buttermilk.
Spoon half mixture in greased 12-inch heavy skillet.
Sprinkle cheese and chopped peppers over mixture and cover with remaining half of cornmeal mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine first eight ingredients.
Fold in crabmeat.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Old Bay seasoning for color.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Add boiling water to raisins; cook 5 minutes, then cool. Cream shortening and sugar together; add eggs and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Add cooled raisin mixture to creamy mixture.
Mix; add flour, spices, soda, baking powder and salt and mix well.
Add nuts if desired.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: asparagus spears with lemon butter
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in tarragon and lemon peel.
Simmer 2 minutes over low heat.
Pour over warmed asparagus spears.

title: orange nut cookies(sugarless)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into a roll.
Wrap and chill. Slice.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned. Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Melt baking chocolate pieces with 2 cups milk in medium saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir just until mixture boils; remove from heat.
Combine 1 1/3 cups sugar, the flour, cornstarch and salt in a small bowl.
Blend egg yolks with 1 cup of milk
and add to dry ingredients.
Blend into chocolate mixture in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils; boil and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat; blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour into a cooled shell. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in small mixing bowl until foamy.
Gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar; beat until stiff peaks form.
Spread meringue onto hot pie filling, carefully sealing meringue to edge of crust.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool to room temperature.

title: saltine cookies
directions: Melt sugar in butter slowly; bring to boil for 3 minutes. Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Line cookie sheet with saltines, side by side.
Pour butter mixture over saltines.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Pour chocolate chips over crackers.
When melted, spread evenly.
Cool in refrigerator until chocolate hardens.
Cut into pieces.

title: southwest grilled chicken salad
directions: Saute mushrooms and green pepper in small amount of oil until slightly browned. Set aside.
Grill chicken breasts and slice into strips.
(May add seasonings of your choice.
I like lemon pepper, onion powder, salt-free garlic-herb.)
Combine greens, mushrooms, pepper, cheese and bacon.
Lay chicken strips on top. Serve with warm poppy seed dressing.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine soups and milk. Stir in rice and spread in bottom of casserole.
Lay chicken pieces on top. Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: eggnog bread
directions: Combine
flour,
baking
powder
and
salt;
set
aside. Combine eggs,
sugar
and
butter
in a large mixing bowl; beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with eggnog, beginning and ending
with
flour
mixture.
Stir
in
remaining ingredients. Pour batter into
a
greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake
at
for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cook in pan 10 minutes; remove to wire rack and cool bread completely.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: charlie's rabbit barbecue
directions: Sprinkle chops with garlic salt and salt and pepper. Brown both sides. Chop a large onion; peel and chop 1 apple.
Put apple and onion in frypan and simmer 5 minutes.
Spoon onion and apple mix on each chop. Add 1 can beer.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
If liquid is needed, add more beer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook
chicken
in 2 or more cups of water until tender. Remove bones and cut into small pieces, saving the broth.
Mix dressing and
melted
margarine.
In
a
greased
9 x 13-inch baking dish layer dressing and chicken.
Add cream of mushroom soup
diluted with 1 soup can of chicken broth.
Place another layer
of dressing
and chicken, adding cream of chicken soup diluted
with 1
soup can of chicken broth.
Top with a final layer of dressing crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cut tops off broccoli and save.
Discard stems or chop stems and use with tops.
Cut the tops off cauliflower and save.
Place the first four items in a bowl and set aside.
In another bowl, mix the rest of the items together.
Save a little of each cheese for the top.
Fold the wet mixture into the broccoli and cauliflower mix.
Place into a large baking dish, or two small baking dishes, and sprinkle cheese and paprika on top.
Bake in the oven at 350° for 35 minutes or until set.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except peanut butter and vanilla in medium saucepan and bring to soft-ball on candy thermometer. Take off heat. Add vanilla and peanut butter and mix well. Let cool some. Beat mixture with a big spoon until fudge starts to thicken and set. Pour into greased platter and let set. Cut into pieces, if desired. Can double recipe for larger platters.

title: dip for apples
directions: Soften cheese in microwave, then mix together until smooth.

title: sprout sandwich
directions: Toast whole wheat bread.
Spread salad dressing on toast.
Put on light layer of sprouts.
Put thin sliced tomatoes on sprouts, enough to cover the whole slice of bread.
Put cheese slice on top of tomatoes.
Place under broiler until cheese is melted.
Makes 2 open face sandwiches.

title: crunchy tuna salad in pepper cups
directions: Sprinkle the gelatin over 1/2 cup water and allow it to soften, about 5 minutes.
Pour the consomme into a medium saucepan.
Bring the consomme to a boil and add the pepper shells, cut side up. Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Remove the shells, turn upside down to drain and then refrigerate.
Bring the consomme back to a boil, add the onion and cook 30 seconds.
Stir in the gelatin until it dissolves.
Pour the mixture into a bowl and refrigerate until partially set.
Fold in the tuna, tomatoes, chopped lettuce, lemon zest, lemon juice, salt (optional) and pepper.
Spoon into pepper shells, piling the mixture high.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours, until set.
At serving time, place each pepper on a lettuce leaf; garnish with a dollop of sour cream or yogurt.
Yields 4 servings. Serving size is 1/2 filled green pepper.

title: pistachio marble cake
directions: Combine cake mix, Jell-O pudding mix, eggs, water, oil and almond extract in a large mixer bowl; blend.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour 1/3 of batter into separate bowl.
Stir in 1/4-cup chocolate syrup.
Spoon batters alternately into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or round. Zig-zag spatula through batter to marble.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: pineapple rice dressing
directions: Lightly saute shallots and mushrooms.
Lightly saute rice in butter or chicken fat.
Chop celery.
Combine ingredients and use as stuffing for chicken or Cornish game hens.

title: tucson dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese and sour cream until well blended and smooth.
Rinse dried beef and pat dry.
Chop or cut into small pieces.
Stir beef, chiles, onion and peppers into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle chives on top.
Bake until edges are bubbling.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: barbecue beef or pork
directions: Cook beef or pork until tender.
Drain off broth and cut or tear in pieces.
Place in skillet with all other ingredients and let simmer until chopped onion is cooked.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well and add pineapple.
Stir in bread cubes.
Bake, uncovered, in greased casserole dish at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: almost monkey bread
directions: The night before, put rolls into a greased Bundt pan. Sprinkle pudding and sugar over the top.
Pour melted margarine over this.
Cover with a towel and leave out on counter overnight. The next morning, bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli-tossed salad(a refreshing way to use broccoli)
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a blender.
In a bowl mix together next four ingredients.
Pour dressing over broccoli mix and blend.
Before serving, top with sliced hard-cooked eggs.

title: coconut delight
directions: Mix oleo, flour and pecans and pat into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Let this cool real well.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and confectioners sugar well and spread over the first layer.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Mix the instant pudding and milk until thickened.
Spread over second layer. Spread remainder of Cool Whip over third layer and sprinkle with coconut and more chopped nuts for garnish.

title: barbecue sauce lindsey style
directions: Mix and cook over medium heat until thick.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal, milk, eggs, salt, soda, oil and corn.
Saute ground beef until done.
Pour 1/2 of corn meal mixture into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle ground beef, then jalapenos and onion, then cheese.
Pour remaining corn meal mixture over top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes single recipe.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Mix sugar well with apples.
Pour mixture in a buttered pan or dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: salmon ball
directions: Put in freezer 1/2 hour and then roll into a ball, rolling in crushed walnuts and parsley.
Keep refrigerated.
Excellent.
Do not omit horseradish.

title: chow chow
directions: Chop and mix.
Put in pint jars.
Process in hot water for 15 minutes.

title: make your own butter(this one's for the kids!  or kids at heart!)
directions: Place the marble in the baby food jar.
Almost fill the jar with heavy whipping cream, leaving about 1/2 inch at the top. Secure the lid.
Have the child shake the jar until the cream clearly separates; an adult may have to help with the shaking at times.
(Don't shake too furiously or you might break the marble.) Once the cream has separated, drain off the liquid; the solid left over is your butter.
The marble will likely be embedded, simply cut through and remove it (make certain it's still in one piece).

title: cheese crackers
directions: Coat each cracker with melted margarine (both sides).
Put on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with frozen sharp Cheddar cheese (not too much), then sprinkle with ground red pepper (not too much).
Stick cookie sheet of crackers under broiler just long enough to melt cheese.
Take them out and let oven cool down to 150°.
Let crackers stay in oven for 10 minutes.

title: our favorite chili
directions: Cook ground chuck over medium heat until done - drain. Combine other ingredients with meat.
Heat 3 - 4 hours in crock pot on low setting.

title: taco pie
directions: Cook ground beef, taco seasoning mix and water together; simmer for 15 minutes.
Place rolls in pie pan (pinch edges together).
Sprinkle 1 cup corn chips over bottom of crust. Next, add the meat mixture.
Spread sour cream over meat, then the cheese and remaining corn chips.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Top with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: meatball stew
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg and seasonings (except parsley).
Roll into meat balls.
Brown in oil in 4-quart Dutch oven.
Combine soup and broth in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add parsley.

title: the world's best cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars; add egg.
Mix well.
Add oil, oats, corn flakes, coconut and nuts, stirring well.
Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Form into balls and mash with fork.
Bake about 12 minutes at 325°.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken in a bowl or casserole.
Cover with lemon juice and marinate in refrigerator for several hours or overnight, turning chicken periodically.
Preheat oven to 425° Put margarine and olive oil in a shallow baking pan and melt margarine.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Beat shortening, cocoa, sugar, salt, vanilla and eggs.
Add food coloring slowly.
Add flour and buttermilk alternately. Combine vinegar and soda; when settled, stir into batter.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Brown ground beef.
Cook onion until tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomato sauce and vegetables to meat mixture and cook for a few minutes.
Mix cornbread according to package directions. Place meat and vegetables in casserole dish.
Spread cornbread on top and bake at 375° until cornbread is done.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Using food processor, blend carrots with margarine. Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, eggs and vanilla. Add carrots and mix well. Spread mixture in buttered 8 x 8 x 2 inch baking dish. Bake uncovered at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, soup, bacon, cheese and half of onions. Spread in casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Sprinkle onions over casserole and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Heat buttermilk and butter in top of double boiler.
Mix flour, sugar and beaten eggs (yolks only).
Stir hot buttermilk into mixture and return to stove and cook until thickened.
Pour into raw crust and bake until crust is done and filling firm. Cover with egg white meringue and brown in oven.
This is a delicious cream pie made often by my paternal grandmother who died in August 1941 at the age of 91.
She used buttermilk from home churned butter.

title: pour and chunk cake
directions: Grease or spray a cake pan real good.
Pour in sweetened applesauce.
Pour in crushed pineapple on top of the applesauce. Sprinkle cake mix over pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut over cake mix. Pour melted butter on top.
Finish with sprinkling chopped nuts over top.
Do not stir.

title: tangy shrimp dip
directions: Add mustard and Worcestershire sauce to softened cream cheese. Add onion, parsley and mayonnaise.
Mix until well blended.
Mash in shrimp.
May need to be thinned a little for right consistency; little more mayonnaise can be added.
Serve with potato chips. Serves 8.

title: shrimp remoulade sauce
directions: Place all items in blender; mix well.
Refrigerate to chill. Use on boiled shrimp.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: lemon vodka meringue pie
directions: Prick
bottom
of
pie
crust.
Bake as directed for unfilled pie crust until golden brown.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt in medium saucepan.
Stir well.
Stir in water, lemon peel,
juice and vodka.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture
boils. Remove
from
heat.
Whisk
eggs in small bowl until
combined. Whisk
in
small
amount
of
hot sauce, then slowly whisk
eggs into sauce.
Return to heat and cook, stirring until
thick.
Add butter to mixture and blend well.
Pour into baked pie crust. Spread meringue topping over pie to edge of
crust.
Bake
10 minutes
until
meringue is golden brown. Remove from oven, cool on rack 15 minutes.
Then refrigerate.

title: swiss steak
directions: Sprinkle steak with salt and pepper.
Combine flour and thyme. Dredge steak in the mixture.
Pound the mixture in with a meat pounder.
Let steak stand for 30 minutes and pound in any remaining flour mixture.

title: italian squash
directions: Place the ingredients in electric skillet on low until margarine is melted; add spices to taste, then saute until vegetables are cooked.
Lastly add 1 cup shredded Longhorn cheese.
Cover, let melt, blend and serve.

title: nana's shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir in lemon juice.
Serve with crackers.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix pudding according to directions in only 3 cups milk.
Put Heath bars in freezer then mutilate with rolling pin.
Put in plastic freezer bag, locked, then pound with a rolling pin.
Use as much as you want to sprinkle on top.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cut out on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for approximately 5 minutes or until brown.
Can also roll cookies in a ball and press with a fork on cookie sheet.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and cook squash in salted water with instant onion. Drain.
Add 4 tablespoons oleo, tomatoes, cheese, salt and pepper; stir to blend.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Melt remaining oleo and pour over casserole and sprinkle with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Will freeze well.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9-inch square pan or 2-quart casserole. Mix flour, baking powder, milk, sugar and salt.
Stir together and pour over margarine.
Top with fruit, adding small amount of sugar with fresh fruit. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: mommy's sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes in water until skin peels off.
Mix potatoes in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add first 6 ingredients to potato mixture.
Warm the milk and stir in baking powder.
Beat into potato mixture.
Consistency should be thin; the thinner it is, the better it tastes!
Pour into prepared pie crusts (this makes enough for three 9-inch pies) and bake at 300° until pies are golden brown.

title: curry dip for vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
Serve with celery sticks, carrot sticks, cauliflower, green peppers, etc.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add Cool Whip. Spread on top of pretzel layer.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: Remove and discard casings from sausage, cut meat into 1/2-inch lengths.
In heavy 5 or 6-quart saucepot or Dutch oven over medium heat, cook sausage until lightly browned, turning pieces frequently.
Spoon off and discard all except 1 tablespoon drippings.
Add onions and garlic, cook about 5 minutes until onions are tender but not browned, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes, breaking into small pieces with a spoon.
Add broth, wine, basil and black pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in zucchini, macaroni, green pepper and parsley.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in zucchini, macaroni, green pepper and parsley.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes longer, or until pasta is of desired doneness, stirring occasionally.
Season to taste with salt and pepper, if desired.
Serve sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Beat in egg yolks, one at a time. Add baking powder and salt to flour and sift four times. Add milk and flour alternately to batter; add vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter. Pour into three round cake pans, which have been greased and floured. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Mix and bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan as directed.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Poke holes in cake with
fork.
Combine sugar and milk.
Spoon over cake.
Mix coconut and Cool Whip.
Spread over cake.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Saute onion in butter and 1 teaspoon paprika.
Set aside, Coat chicken, cut up in small pieces, with flour.
Saute chicken in butter until cooked.
Add onion, sour cream, paprika, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve with noodles.

title: quick and easy pancakes from scratch
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a mixing bowl, combine liquids in another. Add liquids to dry ingredients all at once. Stir until just moistened. Lightly grease skillet or griddle. Heat till hot. Pour 1/4 c batter on skillet. Cook on one side until tops are bubbly and set. Flip and cook other side until nicely browned. You can add fresh or frozen blueberries to the batter just before cooking. Do not thaw frozen berries. 8-10 pancakes.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients and let sit for several hours.
Stir several times before serving.

title: sweet and sour broccoli
directions: Bring 1 cup water to boil in medium pan.
Add broccoli and cook, covered, 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Heat olive oil in same pan.
Add shallot and saute until tender, about 3 minutes. Stir in sugar and vinegar.
Add broccoli and heat through, stirring frequently.
(Mixture will be almost dry, so watch carefully.)
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Stir in nuts. Serve warm or at room temperature.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: aunt lou's blue crab quiche
directions: Rinse and drain crab meat.
Remove any shell pieces.
Cook onion and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Combine crab meat, onion, mushrooms, eggs, cream, parsley, salt and pepper.
Bake pie shell in hot oven (450°) for 7 minutes.
Pour ingredients into pie shell.
Sprinkle dash of paprika on top.
Top with 1/4 cup Swiss cheese, grated.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 6. Anna makes this at Christmas.

title: party potato salad
directions: Combine soups with softened cream cheese.
Add sour cream, green pepper, onion and seasoning.
Put potatoes in 3-quart shallow baking dish. Pour soup mixture over potatoes and stir. Spread evenly.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: diabetic orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water. Mix pineapple and cottage cheese with Jell-O. Stir well. Stir in Cool Whip. Put in bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: rita's enchilada bake
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: raspberry marble cobbler
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Then stir in milk and butter. Spread butter in a greased 8 x 8 pan. Scatter raspberries over batter, then pour over the boiling water, making sure it covers all. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes until it is well browned.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Grease baking sheets lightly.
Start over 10 minutes before baking; set to moderate (375°).
Mix flour, soda and salt together.
Cream butter until smooth and shiny.
Add sugars and cream well.
Stir in vanilla, then beat in egg until fluffy.
Add flour in two portions, mixing until smooth after each.
Stir in cream, then nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop level dessert spoonfuls onto prepared sheets 2 1/2-inches apart, using rubber scraper to push dough from spoon.
Shape quickly into round mounds with teaspoon or chill dough, then spoon out onto waxed paper and roll into balls.
Bake about 10 minutes or until delicately browned.
Remove from oven; let stand a minute, then remove cookies to cake racks.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
It makes 2 pies.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour peaches and juice into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over peaches.
Cut up butter and put on top of cake mix. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pam's crispix goodies
directions: Put peanut butter and butter in microwave for 3 minutes.
Pour over Crispix in large bowl and mix well.
Put powdered sugar and Crispix mix in large paper bag and shake well.

title: healthy casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet over butter.
Stir frequently as meat browns.
Add oregano, salt and pepper.
Set on a cool burner.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Heat in 400° oven in a small casserole. Serve with crackers.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and pepper.
Lightly coat tomatoes on both sides with flour mixture.
In a large skillet, heat bacon drippings.
Place tomatoes in skillet in single layer.
Fry until brown on both sides.
Remove to hot platter and repeat with remaining tomatoes, adding more bacon drippings if necessary. Makes 6 servings.

title: slaw (sweet and sour)
directions: Layer shredded cabbage and onion rings.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup sugar; set aside.
Bring to a boil celery seed, mustard, salt, sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Cover and leave out of refrigerator 4 to 6 hours.
Stir and refrigerate. Will keep 3 weeks.

title: popovers
directions: In mixer beat eggs, milk, flour, and salt. Add oil and beat 30 seconds. Fill 12 well-greased muffin tins half full. Bake at 475° for 10 minutes. Then bake at 350° for 15 minutes until brown. A few minutes before done, prick with fork to let steam escape.

title: sandies
directions: Mix in order.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 300 for about 35 minutes.
After they have cooled slightly, roll them into powdered sugar.

title: lazy woman's cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place butter in baking dish (13 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch).
Heat in oven until butter is melted.
Heat fruit with juice.
In mixing bowl, combine the flour, milk and sugar; beat by hand until smooth.
Pour batter into dish with butter, then pour hot fruit into dish over batter.
Bake for about 30 minutes. Crust will form as batter comes up around fruit.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Heat 8-inch iron skillet in 400° oven.
Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine eggs and next 4 ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Remove skillet from oven. Spray with cooking spray.
Pour batter into hot skillet and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: gourmet cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; peel and shred coarsely.
In a saucepan over low heat, combine cheese and 1/4 cup butter.
Stir until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream or milk, onion and seasonings.
Fold into potatoes and turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
"Dot with 2 tablespoons of butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly in 350° oven.
Casserole may be prepared a day before; wait to sprinkle with paprika until ready to bake.
Serves 6.

title: cowabunga
directions: In a blender, blend juices and water with bananas on medium speed for 1 minute.
Add chocolate, vanilla and tofu; blend for 1 minute.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: corn relish
directions: Boil together last 3 ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Stir together.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt cream cheese in microwave-proof bowl.
Add the other ingredients and stir well.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly (can use microwave).
Serve with pumpernickel sticks or logs.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Mix margarine, chives, garlic powder and white pepper.
Drop by tablespoonfuls into 4 mounds on waxed paper.
Freeze about 20 minutes or until firm.

title: red potato salad
directions: Clean and rinse off potatoes; do not peel.
Put potatoes in pot.
Bring water slightly over potatoes; bring to boil.
When potatoes are soft, dump into a strainer and sprinkle with sugar. Let cool a little.
While the potatoes are still warm, mix in remaining ingredients with a good mixing spoon and break up the potatoes.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Tastes best the next day.
This is a very easy recipe to make ahead of time.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: korean bulgogi
directions: Slice beef against grain in 1/4-inch slices.
In bowl, stir together the sugar, soy sauce, oil, sesame seed, green onions, garlic and black pepper.
Add to meat.
Toss to coat meat well. Cover and marinate 1 to 2 hours at room temperature or 4 or more hours in refrigerator.
Place meat 1 inch apart on grill or broiler.
Barbecue 1 minute on each side.
Serve with rice.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Stir together, but
do	not
beat.
Cook in unbaked pie shell for 1 hour at 350°.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread in pieces and moisten with water.
Squeeze out excess water.
In a large bowl, combine eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add bread and mix thoroughly, mashing bread in milk mixture.
Add pineapple, raisins and cherries.
Mix well. Bake in a large baking pan at 325 degrees for about 45 minutes to 1 hour or until set and lightly browned.
Serve with butter rum sauce or custard-type rum sauce.

title: lasagna
directions: In heavy pan, lightly brown beef and onions in oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and paste, water, salt, garlic powder, parsley, basil, oregano, fennel seed, pepper and sugar.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; add onion and saute until lightly browned.
Add 1 cup boiling water, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Boil 15 minutes or until potatoes are soft.
Add clams and heat 1 minute.
Place mixture in bowls, top with pat of butter and add hot milk to desired consistency.

title: cherry cola salad
directions: Combine water and sugar; bring to a boil.
Add pie filling and return to boil.
Pour boiling mixture over jello.
Stir to dissolve.
Add pineapple, juice, lemon juice, cola and nuts.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch dish to chill.

title: cheesy mostaccioli
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine pasta, meat, soup and spaghetti sauce.
Add pepper and 2 cups of Mozzarella cheese. Mix well. Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top, then bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, then mix all together.
Put buttered bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° until done.

title: hello dolly
directions: Mix butter and graham crackers.
Press into bottom of dish. Mix coconut and Eagle Brand.
Spread over crust.
Top with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Beat well sugar, powdered sugar, Crisco and Wesson oil until creamy.
Add eggs, flour, vanilla, soda and cream of tartar.
Make walnut-size ball and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream
shortening, sugar and bananas.
Add egg and beat until well
blended.
Combine dry ingredients and gently stir them
into shortening mixture alternately with liquid ingredients.
Turn mixture into 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan, greased, and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato sourdough bread dough
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually stir in oil and remaining ingredients.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface; knead lightly 4 to 5 times.
Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, for 2 hours or until doubled in bulk.
Yields 6 cups.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix sour cream, dip mix and lemon juice.
Skin chicken if desired.
Dip chicken in sour cream mix; roll in finely crushed corn chips.
Place on an oiled cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: party dip
directions: Cut hole in top of bread about 5-inches in diameter.
Remove soft bread from cut portion and discard.
Reserve crust.
Scoop out most of the soft bread inside portion of loaf.

title: roasted chicken
directions: Remove giblets from chicken. Trim chicken of as much skin and fat as possible. Rinse and drain chicken; pat dry. Sprinkle cavity of chicken generously with salt and pepper. Combine lemon-pepper seasoning and remaining 5 ingredients. Rub mixture all over chicken, coating the top well. Place chicken, breast side up, in a 4 to 6 quart crock-pot. Cover and cook on LOW 7 to 8 hours (or HIGH for 4 to 5 hours). Serve as is or chop and use cooked chicken in various recipes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 4 to 5 minutes in boiling salted water; drain. Combine soup, mayonnaise, onion, cheese and eggs.
Add drained broccoli and mix well.
Cover with a layer of crushed cheese crackers.
Bake in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole for about 20 minutes at 400°.
Delicious!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes about 100 cookies.

title: applesauce bran muffins
directions: Mix bran, applesauce, egg, margarine and brown sugar; let stand 5 minutes. In large bowl, blend flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir in bran mixture just until blended (batter will be lumpy).
Stir in raisins, if desired.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and cream again.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased, wax paper lined tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until done.
Frost with favorite frosting or serve plain with scoop of ice cream.

title: clogged drain cleaner
directions: Mix soda and salt; put in drain.
Pour boiling water over mixture.

title: fudge brownies
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter and chocolate. Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar. Blend in eggs, one at
a time.
Add vanilla. Stir in flour and nuts. Mix well. Spread in greased and floured 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Be careful not to overbake.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix Eagle Brand and lemon juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well.
Place into 2 ready made cookie crumb crusts.
Refrigerate.

title: texas casserole
directions: You will need a 3-quart casserole dish.

title: quick pasta primavera
directions: Cook rotini as directed on the box, drained.
Cook zucchini, carrots, red pepper, green pepper and garlic in oil in large skillet until tender.
Toss rotini and vegetable mixture.
Serve with cheese, if desired.

title: grilled pork chops
directions: Marinate the pork chops for at least an hour prior to cooking. Then grill or broil.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, almond flavoring, baking powder and milk.
Pour on butter.
Do not stir!
Add the peaches on top of this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "hurry up" cheesecake
directions: Mix Cool Whip, pineapple, milk and lemon juice well. Pour into 2 graham cracker crust pie shells. Chill 1 hour.

title: peppercorn chicken breast
directions: Sprinkle chicken on both sides with peppercorns.
Heat heavy, nonstick skillet.
Add butter and chicken.
Cook chicken until done.
Remove and keep warm.
Increase heat to high.
Add orange juice, cream and tarragon.
Boil, stirring until sauce is glossy and thickened and reduced to about 1/2 starting volume.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Serve over rice pilaf.

title: angel flake rolls
directions: Sift flour.
Add sugar.
Cut in Crisco.
Add yeast.
Add buttermilk.
Knead and place in refrigerator overnight.
Make out into biscuits.
Do not allow to rise.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 15 minutes.

title: cheese and olive tea sandwiches(appetizer)
directions: In medium bowl mix first four ingredients.
Trim crusts from bread slices.

(Save crusts to use for bread crumbs another day.) Lightly spread 1 side each bread slice with margarine or butter. Spread filling on 8 buttered bread slices; top remaining bread slices, butter side down.
Cut each sandwich diagonally into quarters.

title: royal rice
directions: Saute onions with butter until tender.
Add rice, mushrooms and salt.
Heat thoroughly.
Fluff lightly with fork.
Serves 2.

title: poppy seed bread(so easy)
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except the poppy seed.
Beat for 3 minutes.
Add poppy seed and beat 1 more minute.
Pour into 2 loaf pans sprayed with Pam.
Cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable spread
directions: Drain chopped vegetables thoroughly.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water and add other ingredients.
Put in molds for 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add to mixture, add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 325°, time may vary.

title: chicken pie(makes 1 pie)
directions: Cook chicken.
Drain.
Reserve broth.
Mix other ingredients together with chicken, broken into smaller pieces.
Place in bottom of pie crust and cover with top crust.
Cut several slits in top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Pie will be done when the crust has browned and bubbles through top slits in crust. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Freezes well.
To bake, unthaw in refrigerator overnight.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix water and butter together and boil.
In casserole, mix rice and soup mix together.
Pour water and butter over rice. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream sugars, oleo and peanut butter.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, soda and salt.
Make into balls the size of a walnut. Roll in sugar and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°. Immediately after taking from oven, put a chocolate star on top of each cookie.

title: happy day cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix ingredients.
Grease two round 9 inch pans, or three round 8 inch pans, and flour pans. Bake until done.

title: daddy med's dooby
directions: Combine berries, water and first sugar. Bring to a boil.
In the meantime, mix other ingredients as you would for biscuits. Roll out thin and drop into boiling berries. Cook until dumplings are done. Serve warm with Carnation milk.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs in large bowl.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to oil mixture.
Stir well.
Fold in apples, nuts and vanilla.
Batter will be stiff.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 (6 x 9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.
The cake freezes well.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, margarine, baking powder and milk.
Pour into 12 x 7-inch rectangular pan.
Add 4 cups fresh fruit.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.
Serve warm or cool.
May top servings with whipped cream.

title: salmon chowder(quick and easy meal)
directions: Bring potatoes to a boil; partially cook.
Add peas and corn; bring to boil.
Add soup, milk, butter and seasoning.
Break salmon into pieces.
Add to other ingredients; cook until vegetables are done.
Do not overcook.
Serve hot.

title: 24 hour layered salad
directions: Cut up lettuce and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer next 4 ingredients on top of lettuce.
Spread mayonnaise over peas. (You can use a thick or thin layer, just be sure to cover all ingredients real good; this locks in taste.)
Sprinkle cheese on top of mayonnaise; use as much cheese as you like.
Then top with bacon bits.
Cover with Saran Wrap and place in refrigerator overnight or for 24 hours.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 50 minutes.

title: cream cheese mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut into 1-inch cubes. Cook in boiling water to cover 15 to 20 minutes or until tender; drain and place in a large mixing bowl. Add cream cheese, sour cream, margarine, milk, onion salt, pepper and salt.

Beat at medium speed with mixer until smooth and fluffy. (Do not overbeat.) Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch or 3-quart baking dish. Bake, covered, at 325° for 50 minutes or until thoroughly heated; garnish, if desired. Makes 10 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and dash of pepper.
In greased 1 1/2-quart dish, layer potatoes, onion and sauce.
Dot top with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover, bake at 375° for 1 hour; uncover, bake 15 more minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; mix cheese, soup, mayonnaise, onions, bell pepper and pimento.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Melt margarine and mix with crackers.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: glorified rice
directions: Place rice, milk and salt in top of double boiler over boiling water and cover closely.
Steam until rice is tender and milk is entirely absorbed about 35 to 40 minutes.
Combine with pineapple and marshmallows.
Add lemon juice.
Mix thoroughly and chill. Fold in whipped cream.
Pile lightly into serving dishes, each lined with a quarter pineapple slice.
Garnish with maraschino cherries.
Serves 6.

title: quick and easy chili dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir into chili and cream cheese. Cook in microwave in covered dish for 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Stir and serve with tortilla chips.

title: diabetic cherry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Add Coke. Place in refrigerator for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour to slightly thicken. Dissolve Equal in 1/2 cup water and fold into gelatin. Fold pineapple, pie filling and nuts (if desired) into gelatin. Return to refrigerator until firmly set. Makes 12 servings.

title: sunday soup
directions: Boil water; add tomato sauce, soup meat and marrow bone.
Cook until meat is tender.
Add rice and one of variations if so desired or omit rice.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs; stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400°, then reduce heat to 350°; continue baking for 40 to 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean and it is high and puffy.
Cool and serve with Cool Whip and a maraschino cherry on top.

title: oriental choufleur beef
directions: Brown meat in margarine.
Add cauliflower, green pepper, soy sauce and garlic.
Stir lightly to coat vegetables with soy sauce. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Blend cornstarch, sugar and broth.
Add meat mixture with green onions; cook until sauce is thickened. Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: saucepot meat balls
directions: In deep heavy saucepan, quickly bring to a boil onion soup mix, water and 1
1/2 cans tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Mix ground beef, seasonings, and remaining tomato sauce. Shape in 16 meat balls and place them in sauce.
Simmer gently uncovered for 25 minutes, turning occasionally.
(I keep them covered while cooking.)
Serve on hot noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: scalloped corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo in medium saucepan.
Stir in sugar and flour until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk gradually.
Add eggs and baking powder; mix well.
Fold in corn, turn into buttered pan or casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 inch casserole dish with cooking spray.
Mix together ground round, onion, olives, corn, peppers, seasonings and tomato sauce.
Layer tortillas, beef mixture and cheese, ending with cheese (3 layers).
Bake covered at 350 degrees for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve with shredded lettuce, guacamole, sour cream and salsa.

title: zach's grandma's nut loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and set aside 1 (8 x 4 x 3-inch) loaf pan.
In a smaller bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt. In a larger bowl, cream butter until soft and smooth.
Add sugars to butter, a little at a time, creaming until fluffy.
Add vanilla and thoroughly beat one egg, at a time, into mixture.
Add nuts and beat well.
Add flour mixture from smaller bowl, alternating with milk, beating until smooth.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar; cream until fluffy.
Add well beaten eggs, then stir in mashed bananas.
Sift soda with flour and add alternately with buttermilk.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes, or until done.

title: meat filling for sandwiches
directions: Melt the butter in a double boiler.
Stir in the flour.
Add the milk gradually, then the eggs (well beaten) and the seasoning. Cook until thick, stirring constantly to prevent lumps.
Remove from the fire.
Cool and beat in lemon juice.
Then add the meat, finely chopped or ground.

title: beans and more(low-fat, high fiber)
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in 2 teaspoons oil in large skillet.
Add broth and water, oregano and crushed tomatoes. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add kidney beans; simmer 10 minutes longer. Serve over cooked rice.
Use 1/2 cup rice per serving.
Use this recipe for a fast, low-fat, high fiber dinner.
Add a large tossed salad with nonfat dressing.
Add fruit for dessert.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: rice con queso
directions: Note:
1 1/2 cups plain nonfat yogurt may be used in place of sour cream and soup to bring the fat grams down.

title: french lamb stew-theresa shea
directions: Brown lamb cubes in oil.
Sprinkle with sugar and cook 5 minutes.
Season with mixture of salt, pepper and flour; stir and continue cooking 5 minutes longer.
Add bouillon to cover meat. Remove seeds and chop tomato.
Add to lamb with garlic clove, thyme and bay leaf.
Bring to boil; cover and continue cooking for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Add potatoes, carrots, turnip and onions.
Cover and cook over low heat until vegetables are tender (about 45 minutes).
Add peas and beans 10 minutes before serving time.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh fruit ambrosia
directions: Chill and drain fruit.
Toss with coconut.
Mix yogurt and toss with fruit.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Put Crisco in skillet about 1/4-inch deep.
Let it get really hot.
Add potatoes, cut in large chunks, salt and pepper.
Brown quickly.
Pour off any excess grease.
Add cream of mushroom soup and 1/4 to 1/2 can water (depending on how many potatoes you use). Reduce heat to simmer; cover.
Turn potatoes occasionally until they absorb all the soup and are crusty and done (about 30 to 35 minutes).

title: country casserole
directions: Brown beef, onions and peppers.
Drain off grease and combine all ingredients except for cheese in a casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Top with cheese and bake for another 5 minutes.

title: edible play dough
directions: Mix ingredients until dough is smooth, then shape dough into various creatures.
Decorate with nuts, candy, raisins, etc. Makes about 5 small creatures, that can then be eaten.

title: cucumber soup
directions: Put in blender and blend.
Serve cold.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in sugar; stir in oil, then zucchini and vanilla.
Stir together flour, nuts, cinnamon, allspice, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture, mixing only until all ingredients are moistened.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) baking pans.

title: squash casserole
directions: Make a layer of corn bread and a layer of squash.
Be sure a layer of corn bread is on top.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use cookie press to make desired shape.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: the gift cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixer bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups coconut.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove pan and finish cooling on rack.
Cut in half to make two 6 x 8-inch layers.
Spread jam and 1/2 cup of the whipped topping between layers.
Frost with remaining whipped topping. Sprinkle 2 cups of coconut on top.
Decorate with green or red bow.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix and make into patties.
Fry in small amount of oil.

title: toffee bars
directions: Divide graham crackers along lines and place on 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet.
Melt butter, corn oil margarine and sugar together and bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring continuously. Immediately pour over graham crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove immediately from baking sheet. Separate and put them on foil to cool.

title: chicken and dried beef
directions: Line bottom of baking dish with dried beef.
Roll and wrap each chicken breast with bacon and secure with a toothpick. Arrange on top of dried beef.
Mix together mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake, uncovered, for 3 hours at 275°.

title: yummy pork chops
directions: Cut cabbage in about 1/8-inch chunks and place in casserole dish.
Place pork chops seasoned with pepper on top.
Pour soup over everything.
Sprinkle cheese on top, cover and bake at 325 degrees until chops are tender, about 1 hour.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix all together well; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375°.
You can substitute coconut for the nuts or omit both.

title: spanish pork chops
directions: Lay chops in baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
On each chop, place 1 tablespoon rice, on rice place 1 tablespoon celery, then a slice of onion.
Pour soup diluted with water over all.
Cover.
Bake at 350°
for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix and chill.
Roll into balls and flatten or roll into logs. Bake at 325° until done, around 8 to 10 minutes.
While warm, dip in powdered sugar.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: orange cup dessert
directions: Mix Cool Whip and jello.
Add oranges, pineapple and cottage cheese.
Mix well.
Spoon into individual cups or a bowl.
Chill.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Blend together; add enough mayonnaise to spread.

title: broccoli corn casserole supreme
directions: In large bowl combine egg, broccoli, corn, onion, salt and pepper.
In saucepan melt butter and add stuffing mix.
Toss. Stir in 3/4 cup stuffing into vegetable mixture.
Spoon into a 1-quart ungreased casserole.
Sprinkle rest of the stuffing on top.
Bake uncovered 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: "veggie" bars
directions: Unroll rolls and press on a pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until brown. Mix soft cream cheese with salad dressing and dry Ranch dressing.
Spread on cooled rolls.
Layer vegetables on top.
Chill and cut into desired size.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion in skillet. Drain in a casserole dish. Mix the sausage and onion mixture with the noodles, milk and soup. Top with grated cheese and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°. Freezes well.

title: breakfast strada
directions: Pour over sausage mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Grease 11 x 8-inch baking dish.
Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry powder, soup and chicken.
Cook broccoli.
Layer broccoli, sauce and cheese.
Add buttered bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni; blend and drain.
Saute bacon and onion together until bacon is done.
Add bacon, onion and drippings to macaroni.
Add all other ingredients, including juice from tomatoes.
Cook together on low heat for 15 minutes.

title: western hash
directions: Cook meat; drain.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 25 minutes.
Put in a baking dish and top with Velveeta cheese. Heat in oven until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix
flour,
sugar
and cocoa together.
Add beaten egg yolks. Add
evaporated milk.
Add flavoring and butter.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: chili sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except vinegar and boil gently for 1 1/2 hours (stir lest it burn).
Then add vinegar and simmer 45 minutes longer, stirring frequently.
Pour into sterilized jars or bottles and seal.

title: mexican tomato caldo
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except the cilantro, in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 8 to 10 minutes, or until heated through.
Serve in mugs and sprinkle with fresh cilantro.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine the flour, baking powder, salt, egg, sugar, milk and oil.
Add the blueberries.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 15 muffins.

title: spicy seafood pasta
directions: Boil sufficient water to cook pasta.
Dice bacon into 1/4-inch squares and cook over medium-high heat or until cooked and slightly crispy.
Add shallots and saute until clear.
Turn heat to high and add shrimp; turn.
Add scallops when both sides of shrimp are pink.
Stir-fry scallops and shrimp until mostly cooked, about 3 to 5 minutes.
During this time, add the red pepper.

title: chicken with cauliflower and peas
directions: Cut each chicken breast in half.
Arrange skin-side up with thickest parts to outside in baking dish (12 x 7-inch).
Sprinkle with basil and paprika.
Add onion.
Cover tightly and microwave on High (100%) for 10 minutes.
Add cauliflower and peas. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Cover tightly and microwave on High until thickest parts of chicken are done and vegetables are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Uncover and let stand 3 minutes.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: In medium bowl, mix eggs, syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt. Stir in pecans. Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: aunt shirley's
directions: In skillet, scramble hamburger and onion until brown, then drain grease.
In saucepan, mix green chiles, soups, milk and enchilada sauce and simmer.
In large casserole dish, layer broken tortillas, hamburger, sauce and shredded cheese.
Serve.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
To 1/2 cup of flour, add salt, soda and baking powder; set aside.
Add remaining flour to egg mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Now stir in last 1/2 cup of flour.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: double duty dish
directions: Pour dry jello over cottage cheese.
Set aside.
Mix Cool Whip into pineapple chunks; add to first mixture.
Add nuts.
Cool in refrigerator.
Stays well for a couple of days.

title: chocolate pie filling
directions: Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick.
This may be lumpy but just use an electric mixer in it.
Makes enough for 1 pie.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine squash, onion and salt.
Let stand for two
hours and drain.
May let stand overnight.
Combine vinegar, sugar, seeds and peppers.
Bring to a hard boil.
Add squash and onion.
Bring to a boil.
Pack in hot sterile jars and seal.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Drain and cool.
Mix pasta, onion, cheese, pepperoni and celery.
Add Italian dressing until pasta is well coated.

title: tammy's cheese ball
directions: Cut green onions and ham in small pieces.
Then mix cream cheese, onions, Nature's seasoning, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 of ham.
Form into a ball.
Take remaining ham and roll onto outside of cheese ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Mix syrup, sugar and peanut butter.
Cook over medium heat to a bubbling boil.
Add corn flakes.
Spoon drop onto wax paper.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Blend corn meal, buttermilk and Wesson oil together.
Beat eggs slightly and add to mixture.
Stir in other ingredients (corn, onions, cheese and pepper).
Pour into greased skillet or rectangle baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes, or until done.
(Test of doneness:
Cleanliness of knife stuck into mixture.)

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Into large bowl, sift flour with baking soda and salt.
