Add sugar, egg, vanilla and butter at medium speed.
Beat until smooth and well combined, about 1 minute.
Stir in walnuts and chocolate pieces.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove to wire rack; cool.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Fry chicken or bake until done. Add chicken that has been picked off bones to pan and put in soup, milk, and beaten egg. Then add stuffing to pan or make up your own chicken stuffing with cornbread and seasonings.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Add to mixture in skillet.
Cover and bring to boil.
Simmer on low heat for 25 minutes.
Remove cover and cook 5 minutes longer or until liquid is absorbed.

title: chile chip casserole(quick dinner)
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain.
Warm chile beans.
In large casserole, combine meat, chile beans and onion.
Mix thoroughly. Then add cheese and stir through.
Add chips and stir gently.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and then add flour.
Add soda, salt and oatmeal; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, 12 minutes for really crispy cookies.

title: lebkucken
directions: Boil and cool honey, molasses, brown sugar and egg.
Mix in order.
Chill dough overnight.
Using small amounts, roll out 1/4 inch thickness and 1 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch oblong.
Place 1 inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: slye's corn muffins
directions: Blend all ingredients together well.
Bake in 450° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Stir sugar, flour, margarine and vanilla into beaten eggs. Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hot crabmeat appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Spoon into 8-inch pie plate.
Top with almonds and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with raw vegetables or pumpernickel rounds.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute chopped celery and onion.
Cut bacon into pieces and blanch.
Heat broth; add celery, onion, bacon, salt, thyme and potatoes.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Melt butter; add flour.
Heat milk; mix together.
Add to broth and vegetables. Let simmer.

title: dad's turkey stuffing
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until tender.
Add soup and seasonings over low heat; mix thoroughly.
Toss bread cubes and mix well.
Turn into baking dish.
Heat thoroughly before serving with turkey dinner.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine broth, water and potatoes. Heat to boiling point.
Reduce heat; cover and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add other vegetables; cook until they are tender. Makes 7 cups.

title: nana's no fail fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in saucepan, stirring constantly. Cook to a rolling boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, add chocolate morsels and marshmallows.
Stir until all are melted.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread into buttered 8-inch pan. No beating required.

title: al's barbecue sauce
directions: Let simmer; add to meat when you have 1/2 hour additional cooking time.

title: sweet cherry jello salad
directions: Put all the liquid off the pineapple and cherries in a measuring cup and add enough water to make 1 cup; heat to dissolve the Jell-O.
Add Dr. Pepper, Coke or Pepsi to make up 1 more cup of liquid and add to dissolved gelatin.
Set in refrigerator to cool.

title: italian bean salad
directions: Stir together dressing mix and vinegar.
Add all other ingredients.
Toss to coat well.
Cover.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: ham and cabbage soup
directions: Combine all together and cook 25 minutes.

title: noodles alfredo
directions: Slice 1/2 butter and place in warm bowl or chafing dish.
Add cream, parsley, basil, salt and pepper.
Drain noodles.
Pour into warm bowl; add remaining butter until well coated.
Add cheese; coat noodles.
Secure immediately.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Cook at 300° until light brown, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, overnight.
The next day, add the next 4 ingredients.
Pour in a baking dish.
Add crushed cashews or slivered almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until hot throughout.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Blend in condensed milk. Beat in cottage cheese.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
In small bowl, beat egg whites with salt until stiff.
Fold in and add lemon juice.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes, until set.

title: sue's cheesecake
directions: Press graham cracker crust into spring-form pan.
Soften cheese.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add sugar slowly, then vanilla.
Pour in crust and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli.
Cut off long stalks and cut broccoli head into small pieces.
Mix onion, raisins and bacon together.
Top with mixture of sugar and mayonnaise.
Let set overnight to enhance the flavor.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Put ingredients in baking dish.
Cover with buttered Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: spanish soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all the ingredients.
Thoroughly warm the mixture over medium heat.
Serve with croutons or crackers.

title: tuna medley salad
directions: Put tuna, onion, green pepper, garlic powder, salt and black pepper in blender until finely chopped.
Remove and add cranberries, apples and walnuts and blend in mayonnaise to taste. Makes 4 healthy sandwiches or serves as a dip with crackers.

title: corn bread(self-rising meal)
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a greased, heated pan.
Cook at 425° until done (15 to 20 minutes).

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in 1 cup margarine.
Add broccoli and mushroom soup.
Cook rice in 2 cups water, 1 teaspoon butter and 1 teaspoon salt for 15 minutes.
Add the Cheez Whiz. Mix together in large casserole; top with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: minted ice ring
directions: Arrange in an attractive design thin half slices of lemon and lime, maraschino cherries (rinse under running water) and large mint leaves, in bottom of ring mold.
Add very thin layer of water, just enough to touch you decorations.
Freeze.
Add cold boiled water to fill.
Freeze.
Remove by running water over bottom of mold.

title: aunt sue's fresh peach cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 4 layer pans.
Combine sugar and cornstarch in sauce pan.
Add peaches and water.
Cook over medium heat stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.
Cool completely, and blend in sour cream.
Whip cream and sugar until stiff (peak forms).
Layer cake.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix and bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Put nutmeg on top.

title: viennese torte
directions: Melt butter, chocolate chips and water over high heat.
Beat and cool.
Add egg yolks, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth. Cool before spreading on cake.
Slice the cake horizontally into 4 equal parts.
Spread chocolate mixture between each layer.
Pour the remaining chocolate mixture on the top of the cake, letting it run down the sides on to the cake platter.
Chill at least one day or overnight.

title: "ostrich bells"
directions: Cut off the tops of the bell peppers and set aside for later. Mix ostrich meat (uncooked), rice, salt and pepper together, then stuff it in the bottom half of the peppers.
Place the tops back on the peppers and wrap loosely in aluminum foil, then bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Flatten chicken breasts to 1/2-inch thickness. Dip each breast in the egg and lightly coat with bread crumbs. Brown in oil and transfer to a baking dish. In a saucepan, combine tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and butter. Simmer for 20 minutes. Pour over chicken and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake, covered, at 325° for 45 minutes. Remove cover and top chicken with Mozzarella cheese. Serve with pasta if desired.

title: thick crust pizza
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until size of sand.
Add milk.
Mix until dough is formed.
Knead 12 times. Shape crust.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Spread with toppings.
Bake on lowest rack of 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Add all ingredients, except margarine and mix well.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 15-inch pan and add to mixture; mix well.
Pour into the pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: meatballs napoli
directions: Pour over meatballs and continue baking for 10 minutes. Serves 4.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage; add bell pepper and onion to sausage.
Cook until tender.
Drain well.
Mix eggs and milk; beat well.
Pour 1/2 of the sausage mixture into each pie shell.
Top with 1/2 of the cheese.
Divide the egg and milk mixture and pour into the pie shells.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Freezes well.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Sprinkle coconut, pecans and white chocolate chips evenly in the bottom of a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Beat eggs.
Remove 2 tablespoons of eggs to spread on top of the bread.
Add milk to eggs in bowl.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add these dry ingredients through a sifter to the milk and egg mixture and mix.
Melt the butter.
Add to the flour mixture.
Beat until all ingredients are thoroughly mixed.

title: beth's chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets or line with parchment paper.
Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over hot, not boiling water.
Remove from heat; cool.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs, beating well. Blend in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in small bowl.
Add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Mix in oats and nuts.

title: indian (chicken) curry
directions: Recipe passed on from Mother, Catherine W. McCullough.

title: sponge cake
directions: Separate eggs and beat yolks until light and lemon-colored. Mix together orange juice, orange rind, sweetener, vanilla and lemon juice.
Add to egg yolks and beat until fluffy, approximately 10 minutes.
Combine flour and salt; gently sprinkle flour mixture over egg yolks, folding in a little at a time.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff. Fold egg mixture gently into egg whites.
When thoroughly blended, pour into 9-inch ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for one hour and five minutes.
Invert to cool.
Should serve 12.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix
together
with
hands until well combined and form into small
balls.
Mixing
is easier if ingredients are room temperature.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until done.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet. Drain off grease. Warm mushroom soup with half can of water. Slice potatoes into thin slices. Dice onions.

title: weight watchers baked potato wedges
directions: Scrub potatoes and cut into lengthwise wedges.
Coat with olive oil by dipping both cut sides in the oil.
Arrange on a nonstick baking pan.
Sprinkle all potatoes with a dash of salt, pepper, paprika and garlic powder.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes or until crispy and lightly browned.

title: red velvet cake and cream cheese frosting
directions: Sift together cake mix and cocoa.
Add buttermilk, food coloring, vanilla, almond extract, melted butter and beaten eggs; mixing well.
Stir in baking soda and vinegar.
Pour into a greased and floured 9x13-inch pan.

title: amish cinnamon bread(refer to sourdough culture)
directions: Mix well with a wooden spoon.

title: easy microwave lasagna
directions: I like to add extra garlic and oregano to the spaghetti sauce.

title: black currant chicken
directions: Heat skillet to 325° with oil in it.
Place chicken in.
Cook until white on both sides.
Mix jelly and Port wine in pot on stove.
Simmer until berries are gone.
Pour over chicken in skillet and simmer 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is tender. Turn chicken often to keep flavor on both sides.

title: cow pies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and shortening together, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in raisins and almonds.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Chill until ready to serve.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: piggy's on the hay
directions: Line bottom of oblong casserole dish with 2 cans of kraut. Cut up onion and pepper and put on top of kraut.
Next, add 2 cans of kraut.
Spread cut up sausage on top and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until pepper and onion are done.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix all together and pour in dessert dishes or pie crusts. If used as a diabetic dessert, there is sugar in Cool Whip and in graham cracker crust or vanilla wafer crust.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon and put in baking dish. Place bacon strips on top of the beans and cook in the oven, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until onion and bell pepper are done.

title: norwegian honey cake
directions: Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour over raisins in bowl; toss to coat.
Sift together remaining flour, baking soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Beat eggs and sugar in bowl until fluffy.
Beat in sour cream and honey.
Stir in flour mixture just until blended.
Add raisins and orange rind.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch angel cake tube pan.
Bake in preheated slow oven (325°) for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan and top springs back when lightly pressed.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 5 minutes.
Run knife around inner and outer edges of cake. Turn out onto wire rack; cool completely.
Store, covered, at room temperature overnight before cutting.
Sprinkle top with confectioners sugar (10x), if desired.

title: 60 minute gourmet chicken and rice casserole
directions: Do not skin or bone chicken breasts.
Sprinkle pieces with salt and pepper.
Heat butter in skillet and add chicken pieces, skin side down.
Brown about 5 minutes and turn.
Scatter onion and garlic between chicken pieces and add the mushrooms and bay leaf.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add the wine and cook until it is almost all evaporated.
Add rice and broth, taking care that the rice does not rest on top of chicken pieces.
Cover closely and cook 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Roll crackers until fine.
Add butter and sugar.
Press in square Pyrex dish.
Mix next 5 ingredients well.
Pour over crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.
Spread with blueberry pie filling.
Top with Dream Whip.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over top.
Chill 8 hours.
Is good frozen.

title: secret chocolate sensation
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) layer cake pans.
In large bowl with mixer at low speed blend all ingredients 30 seconds.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30-35 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove.
Cool on wire racks.
Fill and frost as desired.

title: four layer delight
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Put into a 2 x 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375°
for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.

title: kentucky corn pudding(great holiday dish!)
directions: Blend melted butter, sugar, flour, and salt.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add milk and mix well.
Add corn last and stir.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325° to 350° (only stir once).
Where done, the pudding will be a custard consistency and golden brown on top.
(Cover last 15 to 30 minutes if necessary due to brownness).
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets.
Peel and slice thin.
Fry bacon; drain on paper towel.
Saute onion in bacon fat until golden brown.
Blend in flour, salt, sugar and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat. Stir in the water and vinegar.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in carefully the potatoes and crumbled bacon.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand until ready to serve.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix the Dream Whip.
Add the cream cheese and 1 cup sugar. Mix together; set in refrigerator to cool.
Crush the graham crackers.
Add the melted butter and powdered sugar for the crust; stir.
Place graham cracker crust in dish.
Add layer of whipped cream mixture.
Top with cherries.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: tuna fish patties
directions: Mix together.
Wet hands and make patties as desired.
Melt grease in skillet and cook until brown.

title: blushing peach fried pies
directions: In a deep fat fryer or heavy kettle, heat salad oil (3 to 4-inches) to 375°.
Prepare pastry for two crust pie as directed on package, except after rolling pastry, cut into 16 (4 1/2-inch) rounds.
Stir together peach slices, candies, granulated sugar and cornstarch.

Place about 1 tablespoon fruit mixture on half of each round. Moisten edge of pastry. Fold over fruit and press edges with fork to seal. Fry in hot oil, turning once, until golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Drain pies on paper towels. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar. Serve hot or cool. Makes 16 fried pies.

title: chocolate monster cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in cornflakes, oats and coconut. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Divide dough into 6 sections. On a piece of waxed paper, shape each section into a 7 x 1 1/2-inch roll.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Place 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and eggs.
Alternate adding flour and sour cream.
Add other ingredients.
Use 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: You take some lettuce and tomato and carrots and then you use some bacon bits and then some cheese. Then you use some dressing.

title: honey graham candy
directions: Melt chocolate morsels, peanut butter and margarine on low heat until smooth.
Add cereal gradually; mix well in a large Ziploc bag (do in 3 or 4 parts).
Add 1 cup of powdered sugar and 1/3 or 1/4 of chocolate cereal mixture; mix well.
Repeat (use full box of sugar).
Spread on 2 baking sheets.
Let dry approximately 1 hour.
Separate with a fork or break apart.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish. Mix remaining ingredients well. Pour in casserole. Cook at 350° about 45 minutes or until corn bread is done. Very easy and tastes good.

title: shrimp cacciatore
directions: Heat puree, oil and spices in a large pot.
Once simmering, add vegetables.
Once vegetables are tender, add shrimp.
Cook until shrimp are thoroughly heated, 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over pasta or rice.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: creamy baked mashed potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, thoroughly combine all ingredients, except 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes, top with remaining cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Cream 1 cup of sugar with the butter.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Beat egg whites stiff and add 1 cup of sugar.
Fold into batter and bake.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add other ingredients and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut butter bar
directions: Heat honey, peanut butter and brown sugar over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Mix in Wheaties and fruit bits; stir until coated.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Allow to cool and cut into squares.
Makes about 30 pieces.

title: magic pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 10-inch pie pan with nonstick spray.
Put ingredients into blender.
Pour into pan.
Makes its own crust.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail pudding cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand and bake at 350° until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Mix all together and form into balls.
Deep fry and drain. (Good served with White Sauce).

title: new orleans pralines
directions: Mix buttermilk and soda.
Set aside.
Mix sugar and buttermilk with soda, butter, salt and corn syrup together in a 2 to 4-quart pan.
Cook until it forms a rather hard ball when dropped in water, approximately 17 minutes from the time it begins to boil. Add vanilla, then pecans.
Stir a short time.
Cool pan in sink filled partly with cold water.
Drop onto waxed paper with a spoon.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut biscuits in half and flatten out. Add little smokies and roll up biscuits. Place on cookie sheet and bake until biscuits are lightly browned.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Butter sides and bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with graham crackers (not crushed).
Beat pudding and milk together as directed on the box.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour half over the graham cracker layer, then another layer of graham crackers, the rest of the pudding and end with a graham cracker layer.
Chill for 2 hours or until pudding sets.

title: graham cracker delight
directions: Steam 3/4 of marshmallows into milk on low heat.
Stir to prevent scorching.
Let cool.
Add remaining marshmallows, cream and fruit.
Crush crackers.
Line pan with half of crumbs.
Add cooled mixture.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: christmas punch
directions: For carbonated punch, use Sprite or ginger ale or 7-Up in place of water.
For really sweet punch, use white grape juice in place of water.

title: easy meatball stew
directions: Rub a 4-pound beef brisket with Rub Seasoning and let stand 1 hour.
Place on a grill fat side up and smoke for about 5 hours. Baste with Wet Sauce and let it smoke another 2 to 3 hours until tender.
Carve as you would roast beef.
Serve with corn on the cob, barbecue baked beans, pickles, jalapeno peppers and a little Wet Sauce on the side.

title: mini marble pound cake
directions: Place chocolate chips and 1/4 cup milk in microwave bowl. Melt and set aside to cool.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and sugar and beat until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well; add flour mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Transfer 3 1/3 cups batter to medium bowl.
Stir in rest of milk and set aside.
Pour reserved chocolate mixture into remaining batter.
Fill four small loaf pans alternately with white and chocolate batter; swirl batter with table knife.
Place on cookie sheet to bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Cool in pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle one can of French fried onion rings on top and bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes.

title: scallop potatoes
directions: Put sliced potatoes and onion in a glass dish.
Mix soup, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes and onion.
Slice some butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients together.
Roll nuts in a little bit of flour.
Add eggs, one at a time with sugar, beating well after each one.
Add apples, pineapple and grated carrots.
Add oil to this mixture alternately with the dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: basque stew
directions: Saute pepperoni about 5 minutes and remove.
Saute chicken strips in pepperoni drippings.
Add leek, garlic and carrots and saute for 3 minutes.
Stir in cabbage.
Add tomatoes, beans, seasonings, pepperoni and chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening and add 1 egg and 1 regular size can of evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Divide in half and shape into 2 rolls.
Wrap in Saran Wrap and chill overnight in refrigerator.
Cut off your roll and roll out very thin for your fruit.

title: popover pizza
directions: Brown beef with onion in large skillet; pour off fat.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Prepare popover batter. Pour over meat mixture, taking care to cover filling completely. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken-green bean casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, green beans and mushrooms.
Add cream of chicken soup, diluted with 1/2 to 1 can of milk.
Add the amount of noodles you desire and some of the onion rings.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.
The last half of the time, put some chow mein noodles and onion rings on top and finish baking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 1 minute.
Stir constantly. Remove from heat and stir in chips.
Spread on cooled cake
or bars.

title: buttered cabbage
directions: Wash and shred cabbage and onion.
Cover with water.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain off most of water.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and butter.
Steam 15 minutes longer.
Remove from heat. Garnish with paprika and serve.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Spray a 13 x 9-inch dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Layer ingredients into dish in the order listed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer lettuce, hamburger, grated cheese, kidney beans, onion and tomatoes, ending with cheese.
Top with dressing:
Thousand Island, sugar, taco seasoning and taco sauce, mixed.

title: poor boy fillets
directions: Shape ground beef into 12 x 7 1/2-inch rectangle on sheet of waxed paper.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients, except bacon, evenly over beef.
Beginning at short end, roll up, jelly roll fashion, lifting wax paper to support ground beef.
Slide roll onto baking sheet, seam side down.
Smooth and shape roll.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Mix soups, chips and oleo into squash.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until the cheese is melted.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Stir all together.
Crumble 3 or 4 Ritz crackers on top, along with a small amount of shredded cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Makes a single crust.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream oleo with sugar and eggs.
Dissolve soda in milk and add to creamed mixture.
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix in apples and nuts.
Pour into large greased pan.

title: crescent lasagna
directions: Cook the ground beef and onion in the oil until onion is opaque.
Add the tomato paste and water.
Add garlic, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook until meat is done and liquid is absorbed.
Mix the cottage cheese and well beaten egg.
Place half the rolls in a pan.
Add a layer of meat and a layer of cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat with the meat and cheeses. Place rest of rolls on top and bake at 350° until rolls are lightly brown and cheese is bubbly.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix brownies as indicated on the box.
Add approximately 1 cup chocolate chips.
Beat cream cheese, butter, sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla with mixer.
Pour half of the brownie mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over brownie mixture, then pour remaining brownie mixture on top. Swirl together.
Top with remaining chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: "more"
directions: Brown meat; add onion and pepper.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into a greased dish; cover with grated cheese.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashion lemon cake and filling
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs, beating well after each one.
Add flour one cup at a time to the bowl that the salt and baking powder is in and sift.
Add to the butter sugar mixture. Add flavoring and bake in layers for 30 minutes or until done at 350 degrees.

title: italian rice and peas
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Heat to a boil, stirring once or twice.
Reduce heat, cover and continue to simmer 14 additional minutes without lifting cover to stir.
Remove from heat and fluff rice lightly with a fork.
Cover again and let steam 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese lightly with a fork.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt or angel cake pan.
Mix well with electric mixer, 3 to 5 minutes.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes, then remove from pan, carefully.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Work margarine and cheese together with hands or wooden spoon. Add flour and mix.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Roll in marble size balls and press with fork.
Sprinkle with red pepper or paprika. Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: corn and sausage chowder
directions: Using a small sharp knife, cut corn from cobs; set aside. Place the corncobs, cream, broth, garlic, thyme, bay leaf and 1/3 of the onions in a large saucepan.
Heat almost to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove and discard corncobs.
Strain cream mixture through a sieve set over a large bowl, pressing solids with back of spoon; set aside.
Meanwhile, brown sausage in a large skillet. Cool and cut into 1/2-inch slices in a large saucepan; melt butter.
Add jalapenos, cumin and remaining onions.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in flour.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Gradually add corn stock.
Add sausage and potatoes.
Cover and cook just until tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Season with salt and pepper.
For a thinner chowder, add additional chicken broth. Sprinkle with chives before serving.
Yields 8 servings (2 quarts).

title: pie crust
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients,
cut
in
Crisco, beat egg, add vinegar and water.
Stir into the dry mixture.
This will keep well in
the refrigerator.
It will make 4 or 5 single crusts. You may flatten separately, put paper between and freeze until needed. Thaw a few seconds in microwave and roll out.

title: baked chicken oriental
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Wash and drain.
Shake in mixture of flour, salt and pepper in bag to coat well.
Melt 1/2 butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Roll chicken pieces in flour mixture, one at a time, to coat all over.
Place in baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle more cracker crumbs on top, then sprinkle more cheese.
Cook and serve.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Crush potato chips and put a layer on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and place on top of chips. Sprinkle remaining chips on top and bake 15 minutes at 450°. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: tomato pie
directions: Mix mayonnaise, cheese and onion.
Put tomatoes, chopped and strained of juices, into pie shell.
Sprinkle with oregano and basil.
Put cheese mixture on top.
Sprinkle with broken Ritz cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes. Serve warm, cut into wedges.
Delicious!

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg whites together.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold dry ingredients into egg whites.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mother fields pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare Bundt pan with lard and flour. Allow butter to reach room temperature.
Cream butter and Crisco together.
Add sugar in 1 cup at a time.
Begin to add flour in 1 cup at a time.
Add baking soda and salt while adding flour.
Add lemon flavor.
Then fold in sour cream.
Bake cake mix for 1 hour. Test cake.
When done, allow to cool or cut while still hot.

title: beefy spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, garlic and pepper until meat is done. Stir in water, tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in tomato paste.
Serve with french bread or cornbread.
Serves:
4 to 6.

title: pecan breakfast bread
directions: Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Unroll crescent rolls and lay on wax paper.
Spread each piece with butter; set aside.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nuts together.
Sprinkle this mixture on each piece of dough.
Roll dough, starting at long end.
Place in loaf pan 8 rolls on bottom, then place 8 on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from pan while hot.
Top side up, sprinkle with broken nuts.
Drizzle topping onto loaf.

title: sugar-free jello pie
directions: Mix jello with 2/3 cup boiling hot water.
Add 4 to 5 ice cubes and melt them halfway, then dip them out and add the Cool Whip.
Mix well with a spoon.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: okra puffs
directions: Mix egg and milk with all dry ingredients. Stir in okra.
Drop a spoonful at a time into deep hot fat.
Fry until brown and crisp.
Turn once. Drain on paper towel.

title: jello
directions: Mix together and put in refrigerator.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Put the first four ingredients in a pan.
Cook and boil for 6 minutes.
Then pour over chocolate and Marshmallow Creme.
Then wait one minute or until chocolate melts.
Then mix with mixer until smooth.
Add nuts.
Put in pan and cut into squares.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, milk, oleo and vanilla in saucepan. Bring to boil and cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter (if desired) and oats.
Stir until mixed well.
Spoon onto waxed paper; let cool.

title: beef-cabbage dinner
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add cabbage and onion, mixing well.
Arrange potatoes over cabbage; sprinkle with caraway seed. Crumble ground beef over potatoes; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Pour tomato sauce over ground beef.
Cover skillet and cook over low heat 30 to 35 minutes or until meat is done.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sausage and cheese strata(adapted from gourmet)
directions: In a skillet, brown the sausage over moderately high heat, breaking it up with a fork and with a slotted spoon, transfer it to paper towels to drain.

title: squash and cheese casserole
directions: Boil squash in salt water until tender and drain.
Mash squash.
Add remaining ingredients.
Combine well.
Place in buttered casserole dish (large).
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: low carb sunflower parmesan crackers
directions: Preheat over to 325°. Put sunflower seeds and parmesan cheese into the food processor (with S blade) until it forms a fine meal with almost a flour consistency. Add the water and pulse until dough is well blended, soft, and sticky. Cover your cookie sheet with a piece of parchment paper. (You must use parchment paper - see note.) Turn dough out onto parchment paper, and tear off another piece of parchment paper to cover dough. Through the top sheet of parchment, use your hands to press the dough as thin as you can (the thinner the better). Peel off the top layer of parchment paper. Use a thin, sharp knife or a pizza cutter to score the dough into squares. (Hint: spray knife or cutter with Pam and the dough will not stick to it.) Bake for 30 minutes or until evenly browned. Break along the scored lines and store in a container with a tight lid. For those counting carbs you'll love this recipe. Each cracker contains just a trace of carbohydrates, a trace of fiber, and 1 gram of protein.

title: mixed vegetable pilaf
directions: In skillet over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook mushrooms and basil 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add broth and water. Heat to boiling. Stir in rice. Return to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in zucchini and carrots. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: amaretto souffle
directions: In an electric mixer, beat eggs, egg yolks and sugar at highest speed for 12 minutes.
Reduce speed and pour in liqueur and macaroon crumbs.
Blend a few minutes; fold in whipped cream. Pour into a 2-quart souffle dish.
Freeze overnight.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix together by hand.
Bake at 330° for 45 minutes in 8 X 12 pan.

title: chunk o' cheese meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients, except cheese, until well blended. Dice cheese into cubes; blend into meat mixture by hand.
Pack into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Pour off liquid.
Cool slightly before cutting.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring as little as possible.
Add vanilla, chocolate mixture and pecans. Fill baking cups 1/2 full. (Put baking cups in a muffin tin.)
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 325°. Makes 20 to 24 cupcakes.
You can frost, if you desire.

title: harvest fruit salad
directions: Cut and peel white membrane from oranges.
Holding oranges over a bowl to catch juice, lift out sections.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of the juice.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Put first 3 ingredients into a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 400° for 6 minutes. Cool. Cream together the cream cheese and sugar. Fold mixture into Cool Whip and spread onto cooled crust. Mix boiling water with strawberry jello. Stir until jello is dissolved and add frozen strawberries. When slightly jelled, spread on top of cream cheese mixture. Leave in refrigerator until firm.

title: light chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, shortening and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Beat at medium speed on electric mixer for 2 minutes, or beat by hand for 300 vigorous strokes.
Add remaining 1/2 cup milk, the eggs, vanilla and melted chocolate.
Beat 2 minutes or 300 strokes.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a slow (325°) oven one hour and 50 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 20 minutes, remove from pan and cool thoroughly on cake rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: addie's pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs; slowly pour in milk in saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil throughout the pan.
Remove from heat, should be thick.
Add vanilla.
If you want to make a pie, only put in egg yolks.
Save whites for meringue.
Enough for 1 pie.

title: grandma fosters' chocolate cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 5 ingredients.
Make a well in the center and add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch cake pan and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and vanilla.
Beat in sifted powdered sugar.
If too thick, add cold milk.
